  "amb_1994_09_93":  {
                         "subject":  "Re: Sun Electric",
                         "from":  "Mike Brown \u003cmike@hyperreal.com\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Wed, 21 Sep 1994 12:08:11 -0700 (PDT)",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e Off the top of my head, under the name Sun Electric they\u0027ve got...\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e   O\u0027Locco (original 1990 release, reissued in 1993 with a different cover)\u003cbr\u003e\u003e the 1990 original is on WAU Mr. Modo and the reissue is on R\u0026S w/out the \u003cbr\u003e\u003e Dr. LX/Cauty bits\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI have a 1990 R\u0026S 12\u0026#34; that has 2 Sun Electric mixes and the first 4 parts of the Orb mix.  The cover has a photograph of a sunset \u0026 clouds, with \u003cbr\u003ethe name of the band and the single in large type across the front.  In 1993 this single was reissued with the same tracks but using Designers \u003cbr\u003eRepublic cover art.  This came out after the double clear vinyl, I\u0027m \u003cbr\u003epretty sure.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e   O\u0027Locco (1993 EP with new mixes \u0026 b-sides)\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e is this the double clear vinyl on R\u0026S?  if so, I think it\u0027s just called \u003cbr\u003e\u003e Sun Electric\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eYes, this is the one.  I don\u0027t have it, so I can\u0027t verify what it was \u003cbr\u003eofficially titled.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Check out URbeats by Readymade on WAU Mr. Modo for a Fehlmann equivalent \u003cbr\u003e\u003e of the Kiss EP.  Very cheezy, but quite a treasure.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eYou have that one?  Can you give me the catalog number, year, and track info?(private email please)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMike\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
  "amb_1994_09_52":  {
                         "subject":  "Jon Hassell",
                         "from":  "David F Maier \u003cdfm8@columbia.edu\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Mon, 19 Sep 1994 13:07:41 -0400 (EDT)",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eThis record (the new Hassell, \u0026#34;Dressing for Pleasure\u0026#34;; the *band* is \u003cbr\u003enamed bluescreen) should be an interesting one for us to talk about.  For my money Hassell is a titan and I love everything else of his (except \u003cbr\u003epossibly \u0026#34;Earthquake Island\u0026#34; and the one with Farafina), so I picked up the new one as soon as I saw it was out.  At first I was disappointed; I love City: Works of Fiction and like its urban edge, but on the new one there\u0027s just not that much trumpet - he doesn\u0027t even play on every cut!\u003cbr\u003eI\u0027m still not crazy about it, but I recommend further listening - some \u003cbr\u003etracks have some *extremely* cool digital sound manipulation of the sort ambient fans in particular might appreciate.  (It helps also if a) you \u003cbr\u003elike Miles Davis and b) you turn it up loud 8-) ).  The production is \u003cbr\u003ereally nice also.  But again, give me another Power Spot any day :-)\u003cbr\u003eBTW, I definitely think Eno deserves equal billing on Possible Musics: \u003cbr\u003ehe\u0027s all over the record.  Check out \u0026#34;Chemistry\u0026#34; or \u0026#34;Rising Thermal\u0026#34;.  \u003cbr\u003eAnd I *really* don\u0027t care who ripped off who - not only is Bush of Ghosts a great record, so is Michael Brook\u0027s _Hybrid_, about which Hassell \u003cbr\u003ecomplained just as much.  (He even has a better case here; Brook played on Power Spot and *definitely*, uh, picked up a few pointers from Hassell).My advice to Jon: Quit yer bellyaching and release a solo trumpet album.\u003cbr\u003eD.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
