  "amb_1994_10_334":  {
                          "subject":  "Strata label (was Re: question abt bill laswell)",
                          "from":  "Mike Brown \u003cmike@hyperreal.com\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Tue, 25 Oct 1994 09:06:12 -0700 (PDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003e does anyone know the name of laswell\u0027s new ambient label. i saw a few of\u003cbr\u003e\u003e the records then can\u0027t remeber the name of the label\u003cbr\u003e\u003e robert.horton@tigerteam.org\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eYet Another Bill Laswell Label.\u003cbr\u003eNo, just kidding.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSTRATA\u003cbr\u003e180 Varick St.\u003cbr\u003eNew York, NY 10014\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThere are about 4 or 5 CD\u0027s on it as far as I know.  They come in solid\u003cbr\u003eblack cases - no clear plastic anywhere.  Plain titles on the front, \u003cbr\u003enothing on the spine.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI\u0027ve heard a few of them and own one.\u003cbr\u003e   Cypher7 - a mediocre ambient band with an AOL account\u003cbr\u003e   Automaton - *great* Dub from Laswell/Gab Katz/The Alchemist/Sly Dunbar   There\u0027s another one that involves Buckethead and treated guitars,\u003cbr\u003e\tthat one was a little harsh for me.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAnyone have any more info on the STRATA label?\u003cbr\u003eMike\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
