  "amb_1994_11_114":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: Ambient-Digest V1 #84",
                          "from":  "as82423@wet.sbi.com (Alan Scully x3515)",
                          "dateString":  "Wed, 16 Nov 1994 15:45:54 +0000",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eREPLY TO /.....\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFrom: Richard Karty \u003ckarty@u.washington.edu\u003e\u003cbr\u003eDate: Tue, 15 Nov 1994 13:48:19 -0800 (PST)\u003cbr\u003eSubject: Scanner\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCan someone recommend a Scanner CD or are they all pretty much the same? I saw some in a shop and I think one was a U.S. release (on Caroline, \u003cbr\u003emaybe?) but I could be wrong - it was just a quick glance.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAlso - does all their stuff sound more or less like the track on TEE 2, which is the only Scanner I\u0027ve heard? They don\u0027t do techno with beats and all, do they? \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ethanks\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eRichard\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e...../\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI only have one scanner album, Ash 1.1 I think, the first one. It\u0027s not\u003cbr\u003eReally like the track on TEE2. In fact it\u0027s just one track on the CD, althoughit does sound more like 2 tracks, fading out and then coming back in. Musicallyit is poor. However it does sample some quite long interesting conversations:a man ordering XXX videos (he says his address on the CD), a hilarious conversationbetween two guys who turn out to be lovers, a rapist defending what he did,a guy ordering drugs, etc. Interesting for the conversations, not the music.Perhaps the later discs would be more sonically pleasing? I\u0027d like to know...\u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;chilled to the point of opaqueness\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-- \u003cbr\u003eAlan Scully             0171 721 3515             alan.scully@london.sbi.com"
                      },
