  "amb_1994_10_250":  {
                          "subject":  "Speakers",
                          "from":  "John.Bus@syd.dcet.csiro.au",
                          "dateString":  "Wed, 19 Oct 94 09:36:15 PDT",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eHowdy,\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFrom: Interstellar Groovy Dave \u003ccamde933@goshawk.csrv.uidaho.edu\u003e\u003cbr\u003eDate: Tue, 18 Oct 1994 01:30:39 -0700 (PDT)\u003cbr\u003eSubject: Re: 99% have no chance\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\tAnyway, what\u0027s a favorite brand of speakers for people?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eB\u0026W get\u0027s my vote.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eObAmbient:\u003cbr\u003eLast time I was over in the US of A I bought back heaps of music (since\u003cbr\u003eits so cheap in comparison to Australian prices). Anyhow i bought back\u003cbr\u003emost of the AI series that I didn\u0027t already have and hence the basis of\u003cbr\u003emy question.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCan somebody give me the correct tracklisting for B12\u0027s ElectroSoma albumon WaxTrax and in particular the name of the extra song that appears on this release? Thanks in advance.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eRegards,\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eJohn\u003cbr\u003e/-------------------------------------------------------------------\\\u003cbr\u003e| JOHN BUS (aka. JOHNNY TURBO)                                      |\u003cbr\u003e| SNAIL\t- Digital Access                                            |\u003cbr\u003e|         Box 13, 7 Sagar Place North Ryde 2113 Australia           |\u003cbr\u003e| EMAIL - John.Bus@syd.dcet.csiro.au OR turbo@twister.apana.org.au  |\u003cbr\u003e|                                                                   |\u003cbr\u003e| On Now: NIN - Fixed (so its not ambient, but who cares! :)        |\u003cbr\u003e\\-------------------------------------------------------------------/\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_09_13":  {
                         "subject":  "more labels-n-such",
                         "from":  "\"Mike R Quinn\" \u003cmike_r_quinn@code20.nl.nuwc.navy.mil\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "12 Sep 1994 16:33:27 -0400",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003ePS WOW!  This Lotus thing is kicking my ass!\u003cbr\u003eexclaimed rbcIII\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eif you like the Locust, you\u0027ll probably enjoy equally Tournesol\u0027s Kokotsu,also on Apollo (a similar kind of buzz).  Two of my absolute favorite discsare also on Apollo:  More Beautiful Human Life! by Uzect Plaush (unscramblethe anagram to spot a more familiar name?) and The Fires of Ork (Geir\u003cbr\u003eJennsen/Pete Namlook collaboration originally on FAX).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHas anyone out there listened to a CD called Kyema, Intermediate States doneby Eliane Radigue?  It was released by the Experimental Intermedia Foundationon their XI label circa 1991.  An incredibly sedate \u0026#34;deep listening\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003eexperience that I never seem to tire of, very slowly changing and deeplylayered analog synth sounds and subtle noises.  I don\u0027t know if anyone sharesmy enthusiasm for this piece but to me its a classic of the genre.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eoh yeah, I just remembered another label:  Barooni (country?) has put outsome great ambient stuff by Thomas Koner (processed gong reverberations assource material if I remember correctly).  Which leads to the group Main\u0027s(who cite TK in credits on at least 1 release) 2 CDEPs and latest album\u003cbr\u003eMotion Pool (Beggars Banquet).  Their 1st album Hydra-Calm I wasn\u0027t impressedby but to be fair didn\u0027t get to listen to it carefully.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003emike \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
  "amb_1994_11_161":  {
                          "subject":  "Global Comm info",
                          "from":  "David F Maier \u003cdfm8@columbia.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Sat, 19 Nov 1994 15:55:49 -0500 (EST)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eDear Ambient Savants:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOn the advice of many of you, I bought _76:14_ the other day, and now, as you could probably have predicted, I need to know what else there is by this artist so I can buy it immediately.  Is Reload the same people (or one of them)?  What singles and/or EP\u0027s are there?  \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThanks-\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eD.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eP.S. Do me a favor and don\u0027t recommend something obscure that only you \u003cbr\u003ehave, although *constructive* showing off is acceptable... 8-)\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_117":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: ambient: fun with labels",
                          "from":  "Joseph Morrison \u003cbrapman@netcom.com\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 13 Oct 1994 13:33:17 -0700 (PDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eOn Thu, 13 Oct 1994, Robert Horton wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e fun with labels. i think labels should be fun or forget them. we don\u0027t\u003cbr\u003e\u003e need serious boxes to stuff things into. boxing is one of the main ways\u003cbr\u003e\u003e of control. we have a spectrum lets have fun with it.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e               the spectrum\u003cbr\u003e\u003e ambient (chill)-----------------------------------ambient (with beats)\u003cbr\u003eI agree with this absolutely.  And the beats are a method of conveying an energy level, as well as an atmosphere (ethnic beats take ME elsewhere...for a single example...).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e=B)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOnNow: 23 Degrees _An Endless Searching for Substance_ ...very nice, very dubby...and has some of the ethnic beats referred to, even.  \u003cG\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
