  "amb_1994_11_270":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: Arcane Device / Stapleton",
                          "from":  "Duguid Brian \u003cBD1@MM-CROY.mottmac.co.uk\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Mon, 28 Nov 94 09:47:32",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eFrom: Harvey Thornburg \u003chthornbu@osiris.ac.hmc.edu\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eSubject: Influences of Stapleton/Jackman on recent trends in ambient \u003cbr\u003emusic\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eIs anyone becoming aware of the growing influence of \u0026#34;tone-scape\u0026#34; \u003cbr\u003erecordings\u003cbr\u003e\u003esuch as NWW\u0027s _Soliloquy for Lilith_ or some of the early \u003cbr\u003eJackman/Organum \u003cbr\u003e :\u003cbr\u003e : stuff deleted\u003cbr\u003e :\u003cbr\u003e\u003eambient music; this is why I look to _Soliloquy for Lilith_ and related\u003cbr\u003e\u003eworks to point the way. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI don\u0027t know what Harvey\u0027s tastes run to, but I suspect this is a bit \u003cbr\u003eoptimistic. From where I\u0027m standing, this sort of \u0026#34;tonescape\u0026#34; has a long history, via the drone minimalists like La Monte Young, Tony Conrad and Phill Niblock. Or do you (or anyone) think that NWW/Jackman offer \u003cbr\u003esomething different? Don\u0027t get me wrong - I love this stuff; I\u0027m just not convinced that it\u0027s a thing of the future.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eAn excellent CD which utilizes many of these concepts is the latest from\u003cbr\u003e\u003eArcane Device, _Envoi in Cumin_.  I\u0027d say this is almost \u0026#34;Soliloquy for \u003cbr\u003eWhat label is this on? Can you, or anyone else, say how it compares with AD\u0027s earlier albums (esp. Trout or Also Sprach Zarathustra?). And can \u003cbr\u003eanyone confirm why Myers is still making music when he\u0027s widely supposed to have quit music for religious reasons? Is this a contractual \u003cbr\u003eobligation thing?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBrian Duguid                 BD1@mm-croy.mottmac.co.uk\u003cbr\u003e182 Cavendish Road - Balham - London - SW12 0DA - U.K.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
