  "amb_1994_10_288":  {
                          "subject":  "David Sylvian\u0027s Ember Glance",
                          "from":  "byron@tellabs.com",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 20 Oct 94 07:59:52 -0500",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eI had never heard of this one prior\u003cbr\u003eto it\u0027s inclusion on Top Ten Ambient\u003cbr\u003eTracks. I\u0027m quite famaliar with \u003cbr\u003eSylvian\u0027s other work, but I have never\u003cbr\u003eheard of this one. Does anybody know more \u003cbr\u003eabout this work?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e                 Thanks,\u003cbr\u003e                    bt\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_09_6":  {
                        "subject":  "Re: labels-n-such",
                        "from":  "rbcIII \u003crobot@svpal.org\u003e",
                        "dateString":  "Mon, 12 Sep 1994 12:54:47 -0700 (PDT)",
                        "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOn 12 Sep 1994, Mike R Quinn wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Other specifically ambient labels?  Don\u0027t overlook Apollo (the ambient\u003cbr\u003e\u003e sublabel of R\u0026S)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI\u0027m just sitting down to listen to Locust for the first time.  I just \u003cbr\u003epicked it up yesterday.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e or Recycle or Die (I hear the back catalog is being released\u003cbr\u003e\u003e domestically, anybody else heard this?).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eDunno.  I have Oliver Lieb and Dominik Woosey (I love his stuff on MFS, Neutron 900 and United Frequencies of Trance Vol.1-4).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Staalplaat releases some great\u003cbr\u003e\u003e ambient material (lots w/ industrial leanings) as does Musica Maxima\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Magnetica (Italy) w/ the likes of Nocturnal Emissions and Cranioclast.  \u003cbr\u003eHmm.  I\u0027ll have to look into it.  POD Communications always has great \u003cbr\u003eambient b-sides (that\u0027s where Ongaku - Mihon on Chill Out or Die came \u003cbr\u003efrom).  Also Delerium has stuff called After 6a.m.  More German stuff.  Quite nice.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-robert\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ePS WOW!  This Lotus thing is kicking my ass!\u003cbr\u003e"
                    },
