  "amb_1994_11_201":  {
                          "subject":  "Instinct Records email",
                          "from":  "Mike Brown \u003cmike@hyperreal.com\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Mon, 21 Nov 1994 07:56:54 -0800 (PST)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eTo those who were looking for Instinct Records\u0027 email address:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eInstinct (Jared Hoffman)\u003cbr\u003e72170.1753@compuserve.com\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIf you write to this address and ask to be added to the email newsletter list, you\u0027ll get a new release newsletter every couple of months.  The old ones are archived at hyperreal.com in /music/labels/instinct.  You can alsodirect other inquiries about the label to Hoffman.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_09_90":  {
                         "subject":  "Sun Electric",
                         "from":  "Mike Brown \u003cmike@hyperreal.com\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Wed, 21 Sep 1994 10:17:12 -0700 (PDT)",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e who are the members in Sun Electric?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eTom Theil and Max Loderbauer, produced by Thomas Fehlmann.\u003cbr\u003eStefan Fischer used to also be in the group years ago, but I\u0027m not sure\u003cbr\u003ewhen he left.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e anyone have a discography for them? \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI am still accepting contributions for a Fehlmann \u0026 associates \u003cbr\u003ediscography, including Sun Electric/Fischerman\u0027s Friend, Marathon,\u003cbr\u003eand others.  If anyone has any information on the Teutonic Beats\u003cbr\u003elabel (does it still exist?) that would be great, too.  I haven\u0027t\u003cbr\u003eyet arranged the contributions I currently have into a reproducable\u003cbr\u003eformat (it\u0027s just a bunch of email messages, mostly) but if there\u003cbr\u003eis enough demand I\u0027ll do it soon.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOff the top of my head, under the name Sun Electric they\u0027ve got...\u003cbr\u003e  O\u0027Locco (original 1990 release, reissued in 1993 with a different cover)  O\u0027Locco (promo only 12\u0026#34; of pts 5-8 of the Orb mix)\u003cbr\u003e  O\u0027Locco (1993 EP with new mixes \u0026 b-sides)\u003cbr\u003e  Kitchen (1993 album)\u003cbr\u003e  Aaah! (1994 album-length EP)\u003cbr\u003eThey also remixed \u0026#34;Do It\u0026#34; by Yello and have a track on Volume 8.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMike\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
  "amb_1994_10_502":  {
                          "subject":  null,
                          "from":  "terremt@mail.med.cornell.edu (Terre Thaemlitz)",
                          "dateString":  "Mon, 31 Oct 1994 15:54:03 -0500",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eFrom: Interstellar Groovy Dave \u003ccamde933@uidaho.edu\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e 117   Terre Thaemilitz        Tranquilizer               InstinctAmbient\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003ePowerful album from this Dublin native.  The controversy generated by\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003eher appearance on Saturday Night Live in 1992, where she tore up a\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003epicture of the Pope, has clearly effected her songwriting.  Her usually\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003elighthearted lyrics have been replaced by a darker, even cynical tone.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e        HAHAHAHAHAHAH!!!!   Terre, you\u0027ve been shaving your head even\u003cbr\u003e\u003emore closely than usual, haven\u0027t you!  And you have...Wow...Terre, nice\u003cbr\u003e\u003edress!   8-)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eall of this seemed surprisingly intimate and accurate... \u0026#34;how did *THAT*picture get out on the net?!\u0026#34; ...until i realized you were talking aboutsinead.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c:)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e     Terre Thaemlitz\u003cbr\u003e     terremt@med.cornell.edu\u003cbr\u003e     http://www2.med.cornell.edu/~terremt/Thaemlitz.html\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_09_142":  {
                          "subject":  "Never Mind The Distortion",
                          "from":  "tntmusic@halcyon.halcyon.com (Kevin J. O\u0027Conner dba Tinty Music)",
                          "dateString":  "Mon, 26 Sep 1994 14:38:27 -0700",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eThe new Nav Katze remix CD, entitled \u0026#34;Never Mind The Distortion\u0026#34;, should be out now in Japan.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI suspect most of you won\u0027t be familiar with this Japanese duo, but neither are most Japanese record buyers.  In fact, ordinarily this group would have absolutely no connection with this list.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWhat makes this particular disc of possible interest to this group is the people who participated in the remixes.  Here is the full track listing:\u003cbr\u003e1. Nobody home (Ultramarine mix - I\u0027m assuming it\u0027s Ultramarine, anyway, as    there appears to be a misprint in the Japanese magazine from which this    information comes)\u003cbr\u003e2. Ziggy (Aphex Twin mix)\u003cbr\u003e3. Never not (Black Dog mix #1)\u003cbr\u003e4. Crazy dream (Retro 313 future memory mix)\u003cbr\u003e5. Change (Aphex Twin mix)\u003cbr\u003e6. More than a feeling (Black Dog mix #2) (yes, this is a remake of the Boston    song, the original mix of which is quite good)\u003cbr\u003e7. Wild horse (global mix communication)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMy copy of this album should be arriving sometime next week, at which time I\u0027ll be able to say something about what these remixes actually sound like.\u003cbr\u003eKevin J. O\u0027Conner d.b.a. Tinty Music   P.O. Box 85363   Seattle, WA 98145-1363             vox: (206) 632-9369     fax/modem: (206) 545-2868\u003cbr\u003e            e-mail: tntmusic@halcyon.com    tintmeister@pan.com\u003cbr\u003e             k.oconner@genie.geis.com    zzs32874@pcvan.or.jp.\u003cbr\u003e  \u0026#34;When the going gets weird, the weird turn pro.\u0026#34; - Dr. Hunter S. Thompson\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
