  "amb_1994_10_513":  {
                          "subject":  "Ambient room video...?",
                          "from":  "Jeffrey Kihn \u003cjeffkihn@ocf.Berkeley.EDU\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Mon, 31 Oct 1994 20:55:36 -0800",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI was in the ambient room at a club in San Francisco last night\u003cbr\u003e(1190 Folsom...Sunday night ambient/trance...really cool!)\u003cbr\u003eand along with the _excellent_ music from Spaz/Planet 6 there was this\u003cbr\u003ecrazy French animated movie that may be called \u0026#34;Fantastic Planet\u0026#34;...\u003cbr\u003eor something.\u003cbr\u003eDoes anyone know anything about this? It was serious tripping/freaking me out.\u003cbr\u003eOn to other things....\u003cbr\u003eFeed Your Head 2 is pretty good. I think I like it better than 1. The\u003cbr\u003eAstralasia track is deep deep trancey stuff...I really like the feel of it.\u003cbr\u003eAbout \u0026#34;Neroli\u0026#34;...it is intended to be listened to while thinking\u003cbr\u003e(e.g. pondering, writing, painting, organizing) and I have heard from\u003cbr\u003epeople who have listened to it in this context that it is quite effective.Never tried it for myself though.\u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;Shutov Assembly\u0026#34; is good, though rather more unsettling than most Eno\u003cbr\u003eambient. It is a must-have, however, just for \u0026#34;Ikebukuro\u0026#34;. Seriously\u003cbr\u003emeditative, intense stuff.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAs far as From Here to Tranqility 3, I should probably let Kim field a\u003cbr\u003eresponse to that.... But just to say that yes, most of the artists on\u003cbr\u003eSilent are unknowns, but the music is seriously good. As exciting as it\u003cbr\u003eis to go and pick up the new Aphex or Orb or whatever, it\u0027s just as\u003cbr\u003eexciting to hear great stuff coming from new faces. And just to make\u003cbr\u003ea weird connection, the acclaimed 23 Degrees did a live set at 1190\u003cbr\u003eFolsom two Sundays ago.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFax! Fax fax fax. From Within, Zenith, and 2350 Broadway seem to be\u003cbr\u003ethe faves after the Air/Silence powerhouse. Any news on domestic\u003cbr\u003ereleases of these, or should I be turning the place upside-down looking\u003cbr\u003efor import copies (especially of From Within)?\u003cbr\u003e\\\u003cbr\u003eAlright...that\u0027s it. I am now officially too tired to function.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e--Jeff\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_09_32":  {
                         "subject":  "Michael Joly: An introduction...",
                         "from":  "Andrew Thomas \u003cathomas@ambient.acs.uci.edu\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Fri, 16 Sep 1994 12:53:36 -0700",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e------- Forwarded Message\u003cbr\u003eDate: Fri, 16 Sep 1994 14:53:37 +0059 (EDT)\u003cbr\u003eFrom: Michael Joly \u003celectric@world.std.com\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSubject: An introduction...\u003cbr\u003eTo: owner-ambient@hyperreal.com\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHi Mike and Andy,\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eJust heard about the Ambient list and subcribed, I\u0027m glad you guys are \u003cbr\u003edoing this and hope it will have an expansive and cohesive effect on the ambient scene world wide.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI co-produce \u0026#34;ElectricSpace\u0026#34; heard every Tuesday from 12:30am to 2:30am on WMBR 88.1 in Cambridge, MA out of MIT and serving the greater Boston area.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;ElectricSpace\u0026#34; is a cyberspace-themed talk and ambient music show that explores the personal and social aspects of new digital communication \u003cbr\u003etechnologies. We take listener call, Internet email (electric@wmbr.mit.edu) have special in-studio guests and play the latest ambient tracks.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI also produce original surround sound encoded \u0026#34;cyberscapes\u0026#34; - they sound like real location sound recordings but they are subltly \u0026#34;amped\u0026#34;.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI\u0027ve thinking it would be great to start a network of radio stations, \u003cbr\u003eclubs, cafe and record stores that support ambient music. Perhaps the \u003cbr\u003eambient list is a way to get this project started.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBest wishes for success with the endeavor. Feel free to forward this \u003cbr\u003emessage to the list if wish.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003epeace and blessings\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMichael Joly - Producer\u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;ElectricSpace\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003eWMBR 88.1 \u003cbr\u003e3 Ames St.\u003cbr\u003eCambridge, MA USA\u003cbr\u003eelectric@wmbr.mit.edu\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e------- End of Forwarded Message\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
