                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e From: \u0026#34;Dmitry Bender\u0026#34; \u003cdb@mark-itt.ru\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Date: Fri, 14 Oct 94 23:55:43 +0400\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Subject: Top something\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e Michael Brook   \u0026#34;Cobalt Blue\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Michael Brook   \u0026#34;Live at the Aquarium\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e[snip]\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Michael Brook   \u0026#34;Hybrid\u0026#34; (collaboration with Eno bros, D.Lanois et al)[snip] \u003cbr\u003e\u003e I spare you of my waste comments, ppl are way too different to try\u003cbr\u003e\u003e convert someone by mail, these are just facts of life FYI.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e NowOn   Michael Brook \u0026#34;Live at the Aquarium\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003eYou may be right about trying to convert people by mail but if I could \u003cbr\u003ejust have everyone\u0027s attention for a moment I would just like to point \u003cbr\u003eout that\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e*MICHAEL BROOK RULES*\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThank you for your time.  Have a nice day.  :-)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eD.\u003cbr\u003e"
