                         "dateString":  "Wed, 21 Sep 1994 22:28:37 -0400 (EDT)",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOn Wed, 21 Sep 1994, Matt Corwine wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e \u003e   Aaah! (1994 album-length EP)\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Side 4 is the best. :-)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAt the very least, it\u0027s the most straightforward of all the sides. I can\u0027thelp but feel it\u0027s a cover version of something familiar, though...:)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\\ \u0026#34;We have come to the edge of a world whichD.A.C. Crowell               |offers us the limits of the accessible, of theAudio Design and Programming |unpredictable; it must be possible for some-The Aerodyne Works           |thing not of this world to find a way through,Champaign, IL, USA.          |something that hitherto could not be found by dacc@tigerden.com\t     |any radio station on this earth. Let us set \u003cbr\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e\u003c\u003e/ out to look for it!\u0026#34; --Karlheinz Stockhausen"
