                          "dateString":  "Fri, 14 Oct 94 14:16:10 PDT",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\tFrom Ken Stuart \u003cken@snowcrest.net\u003e Thu Oct 13 23:10:37 1994\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\t\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\tOn Fri, 14 Oct 1994 04:31:30 +0000, \u003cbr\u003e\u003e\tMixmaster Morris  \u003cmorris@space.demon.co.uk\u003e wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\t\u003e        Apparently Ludwig Rehberg of EMS did all the programming - the\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\t\u003e        band just bought a VCS3 each and he did the rest!\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\t\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\t\u003e        Rehberg is still very active building equipment for clients\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\t\u003e        including   Florian Schneider - and Pete Namlook!\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\t\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\tIs Schneider doing a solo project or is Kraftwerk actually going to come \u003cbr\u003e\u003e\tup with some new material?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSpeaking of Schneider, has anybody ever seen\u003cbr\u003e(let alone currently own) a copy of \u0026#34;Ralf and\u003cbr\u003eFlorian\u0026#34; on CD??\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAn awesome, visionary album.  Hard to imagine\u003cbr\u003eit being made over 20 years ago!  I still kick\u003cbr\u003emyself for letting my vinyl copy get misplaced\u003cbr\u003e(or stolen)!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHeck, I\u0027d even snag a vinyl or cassette copy if\u003cbr\u003eeither were available.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCharly Rhoades       [...] we have just come out of a long quiet period andHaL Computer Systems   we are just remembering how long sounds can last andcharly@hal.com              only now becoming civilized enough that we wanthttp://www.hal.com/~charly/    to hear sounds continuously. - LaMonte Young"
