  "amb_1994_11_267":  {
                          "subject":  "Influences of Stapleton/Jackman on recent trends in ambient music",
                          "from":  "Harvey Thornburg \u003chthornbu@osiris.ac.hmc.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Sun, 27 Nov 1994 17:10:08 -0800 (PST)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e(Copy sent to ambient@hyperreal.com, since most of what I have to say is relevant there as well.)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIs anyone becoming aware of the growing influence of \u0026#34;tone-scape\u0026#34; recordings such as NWW\u0027s _Soliloquy for Lilith_ or some of the early Jackman/Organum material in pushing what can be done with ambient music far beyond the \u003cbr\u003esoundscape/concrete approach of Stockhausen (possibly into something morealong the lines of what Eno envisioned) What I\u0027m talking about is the\u003cbr\u003eassemblage of pure tones, metallic textures and the like to create the\u003cbr\u003eillusion of infinite space, arranged in quasiperiodic movements to suggestan infinite time scale.  I think maybe in the next 10 years we will haveexhaused the possibility of finite, chiefly deterministic approaches to\u003cbr\u003eambient music; this is why I look to _Soliloquy for Lilith_ and related\u003cbr\u003eworks to point the way. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAn excellent CD which utilizes many of these concepts is the latest fromArcane Device, _Envoi in Cumin_.  I\u0027d say this is almost \u0026#34;Soliloquy for Lilith part 2\u0026#34; although not quite as dark. The composer (David Myers) is very explicit about his methods and approaches.  Has Stapleton disclosed anything about his composition techniques (relating to _SFL_)?   \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ejust some thoughts...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-|---------------------|---|----------------|---|--------------------------|-  birthdeath experience --- harvey thornburg --- hthornbu@osiris.ac.hmc.edu-|---------------------|---|----------------|---|--------------------------|-\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_500":  {
                          "subject":  "all the headphone fuss",
                          "from":  "CHOSSMAN@DAVIDSON.EDU",
                          "dateString":  "Mon, 31 Oct 1994 14:56:03 -0500 (EST)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eMy slant on the equipment issue:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI can\u0027t remember exactly who started it, but I took the anti-headphone\u003cbr\u003estatement to mean a personal preference as how to play ambient music...\u003cbr\u003eI for one, prefer to let the music seep into the room.  I\u0027ve tried, for\u003cbr\u003eexample, to listen to \u0026#34;Bringint Down the Light\u0026#34; (my favorite Frippertronicspeice - from Sylvian \u0026 Fripp: The First Day) with headphones.  It just \u003cbr\u003esomehow doesn\u0027t work.  Maybe its just a trick of the brain, but I think\u003cbr\u003ethe varying acoustics of the surroundings contribute to the music...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eChad Ossman\u003cbr\u003eCHOSSMAN@davidson.edu\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_08_23":  {
                         "subject":  "Re:  new labels and FFWD",
                         "from":  "\"Mike R Quinn\" \u003cmike_r_quinn@code20.nl.nuwc.navy.mil\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "31 Aug 1994 13:48:39 -0400",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eRobert Curlee said:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eJust got FFWD.  GET IT!  It\u0027s great.  I\u0027m keeping my eye out for Juno \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eI also just picked up Suzuki - Satellite Serenade on AO.  What else is on \u003cbr\u003eI rec\u0027d FFWD yesterday but haven\u0027t listened yet-\u003e enjoying the anticipation;-)\u003cbr\u003eHow\u0027s the Suzuki?  \u003cbr\u003eI\u0027ve enjoyed /\\mbient /\\/\\usic for many years now and hope that the currentinterest continues to blossom on all fronts.\u003cbr\u003eGood things I\u0027ve listened to lately:\u003cbr\u003e   --Anton Fier/Dreamspeed (Avant)\u003cbr\u003e   --Cypher 7/Decoder (Strata)\u003cbr\u003e   --Create/Charles Uzzell Edwards \u0026 Pete Namlook (FAX)\u003cbr\u003e   --Starseed Transmission/Metamorphic Illumination (Nova Zembla)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLEARN!...TEACH!...SPREAD THE WORD!...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eNow Playing In My Head (NPIMH): Sound System by Drum Club\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e------------------ Nested Letter Follows ------------------\u003cbr\u003eReceived: by Code20.nl.nuwc.navy.mil with SMTP;31 Aug 1994 13:47:16 -0400Received: by taz.hyperreal.com (8.6.9/8.6.5) id KAA17728; Wed, 31 Aug 199410:32:39 -0700\u003cbr\u003eReceived: by taz.hyperreal.com (8.6.9/8.6.5) id KAA17541; Wed, 31 Aug 199410:22:38 -0700\u003cbr\u003eReceived: from svpal.org by taz.hyperreal.com (8.6.9/8.6.5) with SMTP idKAA17536; Wed, 31 Aug 1994 10:22:33 -0700\u003cbr\u003eReceived: by svpal.org (Smail3.1.28.1 #4)\u003cbr\u003e\tid m0qftMD-000C8bC; Wed, 31 Aug 94 10:21 PDT\u003cbr\u003eDate: Wed, 31 Aug 1994 10:21:57 -0700 (PDT)\u003cbr\u003eFrom: Robert Curlee \u003crobot@svpal.org\u003e\u003cbr\u003eReply-To: Robert Curlee \u003crobot@svpal.org\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSubject: new labels and FFWD\u003cbr\u003eTo: shhhh! \u003cambient@hyperreal.com\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMessage-ID: \u003cPine.3.88.9408310902.A8729-0100000@svpal.svpal.org\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMIME-Version: 1.0\u003cbr\u003eContent-Type: TEXT/PLAIN; CHARSET=US-ASCII\u003cbr\u003eSender: owner-ambient@hyperreal.com\u003cbr\u003ePrecedence: bulk\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eJust got FFWD.  GET IT!  It\u0027s great.  I\u0027m keeping my eye out for Juno \u003cbr\u003eReactor on Intermodo.  Anyone know if there are any Intermodo 12\u0026#34;s or \u003cbr\u003eother releases besides these two?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI also just picked up Suzuki - Satellite Serenade on AO.  What else is on AO?  The matrix # is AMBIENT.2 ORAOC.08 and the remix is ORAOC.09.  \u003cbr\u003eAnyone know the first 7 releases, or what AMBIENT.1 might be?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWhen are we going to actually get to talking about ambient?  Test, and \u003cbr\u003eTest 1 2 just don\u0027t do enough for me :)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-robert\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e------------------ End of Nested Letter ------------------\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
