  "amb_1994_10_29":  {
                         "subject":  "Re: Recommendations - Sun Electric",
                         "from":  "Dave Walker \u003cmarmoset@garnet.msen.com\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Mon, 10 Oct 1994 19:39:02 -0400 (EDT)",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eOn Fri, 7 Oct 1994 mr808@teleport.com wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Anything by Maurizio (one of the Sun Electric dudes, I believe).  Check out\u003cbr\u003e\u003e the cut on Excursions in Ambience 2.  I experienced an altered state of\u003cbr\u003e\u003e consciousness while chopping vegetables \u0026 listening to this...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMaurizio also happens to run a truly _killer_ label, Basic Channel.\u003cbr\u003eWhile I\u0027d really only call the \u0026#34;Radiance\u0026#34; and \u0026#34;Quadrant Dub\u0026#34; releases \u003cbr\u003eambient, everything on the label is deeply, deeply trancy (in the \u003cbr\u003eoriginal sense of the word, not in the current sense of \u0026#34;a bunch of \u003cbr\u003ewarmed over dishwater records lacking in memorable melody or rhythm\u0026#34;)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-----------------------------------------------------------------\u003cbr\u003edave walker                             \u003cbr\u003emarmoset@msen.com           new frontiers in pleasure management\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cA HREF=\u0026#34;http://www.msen.com/~marmoset/\u0026#34;\u003eDave Walker\u003c/A\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
  "amb_1994_10_445":  {
                          "subject":  "UVX, Magic Eye label",
                          "from":  "chowe@world.std.com (ewoH sirhC)",
                          "dateString":  "Sat, 29 Oct 1994 14:43:30 -0400",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eJust discovered \u0026#34;Double Helix\u0026#34; by UVX.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI think it\u0027s pretty good. Some of the samples seem to be mixed in in a\u003cbr\u003eslightly amateurish fashion, but there are some really impressive \u003cbr\u003eseamless audio morphs from the straight-up 4/4 dance to really spacy DUB!It\u0027s on the Magic Eye label, which seems to put out stuff of consistentlyhigh quality. But, I only know of three releases on this label:\u003cbr\u003e\t\u003cbr\u003e\tUVX\u003cbr\u003e\tAstralasia\u003cbr\u003e\tMushroom (may not be the complete name?)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCan anybody add to this list?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThanks, \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-Chris.\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_09_178":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: Robert Rich recommendations?",
                          "from":  "ebrandt@muddcs.cs.hmc.edu (Eli Brandt)",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 29 Sep 1994 13:09:20 -0700 (PDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003e -- and have seen a few of his albums in stores, but: Well, frankly I noticed\u003cbr\u003e\u003e that they\u0027re on the Hearts Of Space label and (no offense to space-music\u003cbr\u003e\u003e fans) that quite puts me off. Am I being unreasonable here?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI\u0027m not familiar with most of his work, but I have _Propagation_, and\u003cbr\u003eyes, it does have a bit of a newagy feel to it.  Breathy flutes,\u003cbr\u003echunky organic percussion, that sort of thing.  And the use of just\u003cbr\u003eintonation throughout gives it a sweeter tonality than it would\u003cbr\u003eotherwise have had.  If this sort of thing makes you gag, stay away,\u003cbr\u003ebut the music, style aside, isn\u0027t bad.  Turn it down and go do\u003cbr\u003esomething else -- this is the ambient list, after all.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e   Eli   ebrandt@hmc.edu\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_09_245":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: Money, Equipment and stuff",
                          "from":  "Number19@aol.com",
                          "dateString":  "Sat, 01 Oct 94 00:18:34 EDT",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eAs one who attempts to create ambient music, and who has nothing in\u003cbr\u003ecomparison to the equipment mentioned by FSOL and Mixmaster Morris, I\u0027d liketo say resources are only part of the equation. Having the equipment is onething, but making it do something is another. Even though they are machines,there is the manipulation factor -- it ain\u0027t what you got but what you dowith it. Which I guess holds true whether you\u0027re equipment rich or poor. \u003cbr\u003eI started off sequencing on an Alesis HR-16 drum machine MIDI\u0027d-up to\u003cbr\u003eassigned notes on my keyboard, and using the sustain pedal for effect. Eventhough I had just two pieces of equipment to work with, the results werequite impressive. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOf course, now that I have more equipment, I go back and listen to that stuffand cringe. But the ideas are still there: and when it comes down to it,songs are just ideas. They must be created by composers and played by\u003cbr\u003emusicians (neither of which I purport to be -- I just like making noise).\u003cbr\u003eCome to think of it though, didn\u0027t Mixmaster Morris give thanks to his\u003cbr\u003esampler in the liner notes of _Flying High_? Maybe the damn thing *is* human.\u003cbr\u003ePeace, 19.\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_346":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: darkambient...",
                          "from":  "chowe@world.std.com (ewoH sirhC)",
                          "dateString":  "Wed, 26 Oct 1994 12:10:47 -0400 (EDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e ...anyone familiar with the new wave of gothic ambient stuff out \u003cbr\u003e\u003e there?  I haven\u0027t heard much (death in June, Current 93, Dead Can \u003cbr\u003e\u003e Dance), and have liked what i heard.  Mostof te stuff I\u0027m buying \u003cbr\u003e\u003e now is cheery.  I\u0027d like something a little more fitting for this \u003cbr\u003e\u003e upcoming holiday!  :)\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e Tifareth\u003cbr\u003e\u003e ssmith@unf6.cis.unf.edu\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCheck out anything on the Projekt or C\u0027est La Mort labels.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFor example, Black Tape For a Blue Girl and Judgement of Paris, respectively.\u003cbr\u003e-Chris\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e~r .sigambient\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
