                          "from":  "Andrew Thomas \u003cathomas@hydra.acs.uci.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 29 Sep 94 19:55:34 -0700",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBe careful when using the words subscr!be and unsubscr!be when posting\u003cbr\u003eto the list, majordomo greps for these and interprets them as admin\u003cbr\u003erequests.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFYI We will only unsubscribe people if they persist in being\u003cbr\u003edisruptive to the list.  But please, try to be mellow, this is an\u003cbr\u003eambient list after all. :)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAndy\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e------- Forwarded Message\u003cbr\u003eDate: Thu, 29 Sep 1994 18:34:32 -0700\u003cbr\u003eTo: rbcIII \u003crobot@svpal.org\u003e, shhhh! \u003cambient@hyperreal.com\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFrom: mwinton@uclink.berkeley.edu (Michael Winton)\u003cbr\u003eSubject: Re: *ELECTRONIC blah, blah, blah.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAt  4:44 PM 9/29/94 -0700, rbcIII wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003eWill somebody unsub this guy?  It may suprise you DOG but we happen to \u003cbr\u003e\u003elike ambient here on this list.  \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ePlease don\u0027t unsubscribe him.  He started the most interesting thread thismailing list has seen since it began.  I don\u0027t agree with many of his\u003cbr\u003eattitudes, but look at the follow up posts--I have really enjoyed the\u003cbr\u003ediscussion:)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e-robert\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003ePS sorry for posting so much, but this nutter has struck a nerve.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eTrue, but look what\u0027s come out of it...  \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e(right now I\u0027m listening to Namlook-Silence.  Just came home with it todayand I am wonderfully happy:):):):)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003emike\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e------- End of Forwarded Message\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
