  "amb_1994_10_295":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: 99% (Enigma)",
                          "from":  "jbuzza@cix.compulink.co.uk (Jon Burrell)",
                          "dateString":  "Sun, 16 Oct 94 15:45 BST-1",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eMixmaster Morris said:\u003cbr\u003e\u003e        enigma are to ambient music\u003cbr\u003e\u003e        what 2 untalented are to techno\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe book with Trance Europe Express 2 had an interesting little story on Enigma. Apparently their \u0027Out of the Deep\u0027 track is a reworking of APL\u0027s \u0027The Calling\u0027. Large sums of money were paid to APL which was expected to pay for their studio. IMO Enigma are typical of the predatory major label attitude to developing styles of music.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ejbuzza@cix.compulink.co.uk (Jon Burrell)...Space,Time.Grooving\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
