  "amb_1994_09_83":  {
                         "subject":  "Re: Michael E. Clay: Thanks and a Beginnings Comment",
                         "from":  "\"Ken Stuart\" \u003cken@snowcrest.net\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Tue, 20 Sep 94 23:21:04 PDT",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eThe esteemed Michael E. Clay wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003e A comment about its start ( in electronic\u0027s form ) Of late I\u0027ve noticed\u003cbr\u003e\u003e that Eno is most always mentioned as the \u0026#34;originator\u0026#34; of the electronic\u003cbr\u003e\u003e ambient music but personally I\u0027ve always assigned that \u0026#34;honor\u0026#34; to\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Wendy (then Walter) Carlos. Sonic Seasonings released in 1972 prior to\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Eno\u0027s ambient works was the double album piece in mind. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThank you Michael for bringing Sonic Seasonings to the attention of the readers!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHowever, if we are talking, in true trainspotter fashion :-), about dates then it should be noted that \u0026#34;The Heavenly Music Corporation\u0026#34; by Fripp \u0026 Eno was recorded on September 8, 1972.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAnd Klaus Schulze\u0027s Irrlicht was recorded in 1972 and Faust pre-dates them all with music similar to \u0026#34;Chill Out\u0026#34; dating from 1971.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBut the original album of this sort was Popol Vuh\u0027s \u0026#34;Affenstunde\u0026#34; from \u003cbr\u003eJanuary 1971.  I\u0027ll quote Steven Freeman\u0027s excellent Popol Vuh article in Audion#8 :\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;This album caused quite a stir, hardly surprising as it\u0027s one of the first to implement the moog in a non-classical setting.  Reviews such as \u003cbr\u003e\u0027mystical voyage through a gargling flowing, strange sound world\u0027(Pop), appearances on the \u0027Beat Club\u0027 TV programme and in the film \u0027Rock in \u003cbr\u003eDeutschland\u0027, and Affenstunde making the top 10 LP lists, shows this.  As does their being voted fourth \u0027Newcomer band of the year\u0027 in the (German) Sounds readers poll of 1971.  It also predates Tangerine Dream\u0027s ZEIT \u003cbr\u003e(which Florian [of Popol Vuh] guested on [another early ambient work]), Eberhard Schoener\u0027s MEDITATION and Walter Carlos\u0027 critically acclaimed opus SONIC SEASONINGS.\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e---\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIf I have the story correct, Florian soon tired of the Moog and sold or gave it to Klaus Schulze, the result being that Schulze gave up playing the drums...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003erespect to all,\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eKen            ken@snowcrest.net   (primary address)\u003cbr\u003e               (if no answer, try ken.stuart@tigerteam.org )\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
