  "amb_1994_11_175":  {
                          "subject":  "Plastikman in Florida ",
                          "from":  "Oscillate@aol.com",
                          "dateString":  "Sun, 20 Nov 1994 10:26:02 -0500",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eOnce again, a little reminder of this amazing upcoming event...\u003cbr\u003eSpace is limited, so if any of you Florida ambientos/idm\u0027ers are coming, youmay want to e-mail me no later than this Friday, 26 November and I\u0027ll ensureyou and your party are reserved space for this party.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOrion \u003cbr\u003e---------------------\u003cbr\u003eForwarded message:\u003cbr\u003eFrom: Oscillate@aol.com\u003cbr\u003eSender: owner-idm@hyperreal.com\u003cbr\u003eTo: ambient@hyperreal.com\u003cbr\u003eCC: idm@hyperreal.com\u003cbr\u003eDate: 94-11-09 11:20:44 EST\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eTo all of you idm\u0027ers and ambientos in the SE U.S. or those European friendswho will be in the States, we thought we\u0027d let you know about this amazingevent...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eTRiP Productions presents \u003cbr\u003eOASiS\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCelebrate one year of ambient awakenings and electronic voyages by welcomingour very special guest\u003cbr\u003eRICHIE HAWTIN\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ewith your hosts:\u003cbr\u003eGrumpy (OASiS Ambient Sound System, FL)\u003cbr\u003eOrion (OASiS)\u003cbr\u003eMatty (OASiS)\u003cbr\u003eand \u003cbr\u003eMagoo (Sarasota, FL)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSunday November 27, 1994 @ Kanega 1528 Main Street, Sarasota Florida, 8p-3a  \u003cbr\u003eOnly $6.00\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e(Arrive early. space is limited)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis is Richie\u0027s only ambient gig in Florida and his only Central Floridaappearance and we are proud to be celebrating OASiS\u0027 One year anniversarywith him as our guest.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFor information e-mail to this address, or call (0101) 813.238.0310\u003cbr\u003eor fax 0101. 813.876.7473.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHope to see some of you there!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eDJ Orion\u003cbr\u003eOASiS/TRiP Magazeen\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_11_110":  {
                          "subject":  "fsol",
                          "from":  "dj Lovegrove \u003clovegrov@clark.net\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Tue, 15 Nov 1994 18:15:19 -0500 (EST)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003ealright, a lot of people have asked me where i found the \u0026#34;smokin japanesebabes\u0026#34; single by Far Out Son Of Lung (future sound of london in disguise).i got my copy from modern music (modmusic@clark.net), however it was theironly copy :\u003c.  they are trying to obtain more, since their has been interestin the single (when people found out it was fsol). stay tuned. pj dorsey ofmodern music will post any success in getting more copies.  MAYBE, if weare lucky, astralwerks will release this amazing single in the u.s.!!???!!\u003cbr\u003ein the mean-time modern music does an excellent ambient mail order \u003cbr\u003ebusiness. they have ordered some fantastic hard to find danish and finishrecords, which they will post more about.  their phone # is 410 523 1882ask for pj and tell him RETINA sent you!\u003cbr\u003edj lovegrove\u003cbr\u003e                \u003cbr\u003e                          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\u003cbr\u003e                               RETINA fanzine \u003cbr\u003e                           sonic soul productions \u003cbr\u003e                               baltimore, md\u003cbr\u003e                                410.628.0241  \u003cbr\u003e                          \u003cbr\u003e                          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~     \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_11_214":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: TANGENTS",
                          "from":  "BIGGERSTAFF THAD LEWIS \u003cthad@falcon.cc.ukans.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Mon, 21 Nov 1994 21:15:09 -0600 (CST)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e Jon Drukman said -\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e JD\u003e Another Fine Day: \u0026#34;Life Before Land\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e\u003e JD\u003e Beyond Records RBADCD7\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e JD\u003e This is a different story!  This is a wild, amazing trip into realms\u003cbr\u003e\u003e JD\u003e hitherto left unexplored by ambient creators.  Spacy and electronic,\u003cbr\u003e\u003e JD\u003e with deep FSOL-esque synth blasts wrapped around almost jazzy acoustic\u003cbr\u003e\u003e JD\u003e sounding stuff.  There\u0027s some upright bass and flute parts that sound\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI ditto the recomendation of Another Fine Day- yes- Another \u003cbr\u003erecomendation! :)  Wonderful organic ambience to soothe the stress from the bones...ahhhhhhhh............pick it up and lie down for a listen.\u003cbr\u003eTrack three is one of my current favorites of everything I own, but then this has been said before....\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-Thad\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_390":  {
                          "subject":  "another laswell label subharmonic",
                          "from":  "robert.horton@tigerteam.org (Robert Horton)",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 27 Oct 1994 19:37:42 GMT",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003ewell i picked up Chaos Face on laswell\u0027s subharmonic label. is it\u003cbr\u003eambient, well a couple of pieces are. some are walls of sound that poundyou up against the wall. its great but not easy listening. the ambinet\u003cbr\u003epieces i\u0027m taping onto one tape the others onto another as they are\u003cbr\u003ereally different moods, you could say. the music seems to be made by\u003cbr\u003elaswell and robert musso.\u003cbr\u003eanyone else heard it?\u003cbr\u003erobert.horton@tigerteam.org\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
