  "amb_1994_09_50":  {
                         "subject":  "Re: opinions of instinct discs....",
                         "from":  "Number19@aol.com",
                         "dateString":  "Mon, 19 Sep 94 12:45:43 EDT",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003ethe one ambient disk release from Instinct that I own is one of those\u003cbr\u003elicensed jobbies, this one from em:t, the ambient subsid of t:me. I love allthe progressive house coming out on t:me, so I was real happy to see Instinctpick this one up -- more of an urban/world-style ambient tip (not very\u003cbr\u003espace/drone, or experimental, a la the Exursions in Ambience series). \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOverall, I\u0027d have to commend Instinct for helping these indie labels reach awider audience, and for saving us the high import prices.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ePeace, 19.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
