  "amb_1994_09_171":  {
                          "subject":  "Robert Rich recommendations?",
                          "from":  "\"Jens Alfke\" \u003cjens_alfke@powertalk.apple.com\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "29 Sep 1994 09:49:04 -0700",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eCan someone recommend some good Robert Rich albums? I liked his track \u0026#34;LiquidAir\u0026#34; on From Here To Tranquility #2 -- derivative of Harold Budd though it is-- and have seen a few of his albums in stores, but: Well, frankly I noticedthat they\u0027re on the Hearts Of Space label and (no offense to space-musicfans) that quite puts me off. Am I being unreasonable here?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eJens Alfke ........ OpenDoc Geometer ........ jens_alfke@powertalk.apple.com     \u003cbr\u003e                          Do not taunt Happy Fun Ball.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_194":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: VHS Mastering",
                          "from":  "Interstellar Groovy Dave \u003ccamde933@goshawk.csrv.uidaho.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Sun, 16 Oct 1994 22:58:25 -0700 (PDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003e some confusion here.  \u0026#34;CDs are/were mastered from videotape\u0026#34; generally\u003cbr\u003e\u003e refers to the use of a Sony 1630 digital format for storing _digitized_ \u003cbr\u003e\u003e audio on a video tape before mastering the CD.  You have to use a special\tYeah, I think that\u0027s how you use VHS tape for Mastering.  For \u003cbr\u003eregular playback though, using a VHS tape at Standard Play is of nearly equal quality to a CD, but with that wonderful Warm Analog Feel (tm).  8-)\u003cbr\u003e\tActually, I\u0027d like to try some test tracks.  As far as I\u0027m \u003cbr\u003econcerned, most of the stuff that I do will appear on cassette anyway, so I\u0027m not going to fret if I don\u0027t have CD quality for my master tape, that just means less expense overall.  If I do a mix on a VHS tape though, now THAT would be fun!  6 hours of pure bliss.  A bit stressful to mix, but oh well, I\u0027m a Ambient Mixing Stress Junky (tm) I guess.  8-)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\tHmmm, I\u0027d better hurry up and copyright those phrases so that I \u003cbr\u003ecan charge people for using them.  8-)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\t\t\tGroovy Dave\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-----------*------------*-----------*-----------*---------------*------------- \\ /\u003cbr\u003e 0 0    *------------* \tcamde933@uidaho.edu   Groovy Dave\u0027s House of Fish  |     |Groovy Dave!|  241 Wallace Center    KUOI 89.3 FM Moscow\u003cbr\u003e\\___/\t*------------*\tMoscow, ID 83843      Friday\u0027s 10pm -- 2am\u003cbr\u003e\t\t\t(208) 885-8171\u003cbr\u003e\t\t\t\t\t      My Nipples Explode with Delight!\u003cbr\u003eGAT d++@ -p+ c++(++++) l u++ e+/* m* s/++ n+@ h f(+) g+ w++++ t r+ y+**/--For more silliness:  http://www.uidaho.edu/~camde933\u003cbr\u003e-----------*------------*------SPAM-*-----------*---------------*-------------\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_394":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: Sheesh! (was Re: Fave speakers...)",
                          "from":  "\"Ken Stuart\" \u003cken@snowcrest.net\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 27 Oct 94 18:29:15 PDT",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eOn Thu, 27 Oct 1994 14:51:09 -0700 (PDT), \u003cbr\u003eChris.Hilker  \u003ccspot@hyperreal.com\u003e wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e Please take this discussion to the rec.audio.* hierarchy, and take the \u0026#34;I\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e want to make music!\u0026#34; thread to rec.music.makers.* - if I were interested\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e in hearing people\u0027s opinions of gear, I\u0027d read these groups.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003eand some people on the list _cannot_ read newsgroups. \u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eSounds like a personal problem to me.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u0027Fraid not.  I have a choice of two sites - $5/month, unlimited e-mail, 3 hours/day, incl. 2 newsgroups OR $1/hour incl all newsgroups (min. \u003cbr\u003e$25/month).  So, clearly USENET is expensive, at least to me...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003eimho, considering the\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003eobvious fact that something like half the people on this list either create\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003eambient music or would like to but don\u0027t know how to get started, \u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eObvious fact? What are you, a mind reader? Considering the provable fact\u003cbr\u003e\u003ethat there are 497 people on the interactive and digested versions of this\u003cbr\u003e\u003elist, and the provable fact that only 105 of them had posted to the list\u003cbr\u003e\u003eby the end of September, there are many more lurkers who have never posted\u003cbr\u003e\u003ethan there are list members  who have. I grant that my figure for the\u003cbr\u003e\u003enumber of posters is not up to date, but I don\u0027t believe I\u0027ve seen 150\u003cbr\u003e\u003enew \u0026#34;From:\u0026#34; lines in my ambient mail folder this month. The lurkers are a\u003cbr\u003e\u003emajority.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eIf you meant to say that half the people who post are interested, that \u003cbr\u003e\u003ejust goes to show how small a minority really is interested in talk about \u003cbr\u003e\u003emaking music.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCome on, Chris, you *know* that this is true for all lists, most people are lurkers.  I\u0027ve been on lists with 15 people and only 3 would post. :-)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ePeople who will not say either yes or no can not expect to be counted.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMost people on this list are music makers.  I did a tape trade with someone on the list, and was \u0026#34;surprised\u0026#34; to find a promo tape added in my package,and was more surpised to find it was his fifth album.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIs there anyone on this list who doesn\u0027t make music? :-)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ePS However, I agree that recommendations should be e-mailed, rather than posted, then a sysnopsis posted by the questioner.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003erespect to all,\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eKen            ken@snowcrest.net   (primary address)\u003cbr\u003e               (if no answer, try ken.stuart@tigerteam.org )\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
