  "amb_1994_10_362":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: Ok...next question....",
                          "from":  "BIGGERSTAFF THAD LEWIS \u003cthad@falcon.cc.ukans.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Wed, 26 Oct 1994 21:26:14 -0500 (CDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eOn Wed, 26 Oct 1994, Dan Nicholson wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e midi is out of the question for you for making ambient with only a\u003cbr\u003e\u003e soundblaster. what you\u0027re going to want is a \u0026#34;tracker music\u0026#34; program, like\u003cbr\u003e\u003e ScreamTracker 3.01b or MultiTrack Module Editor 1.1b. these programs let\u003cbr\u003e\u003e you sequence multiple tracks using samples (like .VOCs, .WAVs, or raw SND\u003cbr\u003e\u003e files) and you can get really great results considering the hardware if you\u003cbr\u003e\u003e work with them. You can get both programs on ftp.eng.ufl.edu in the\u003cbr\u003e\u003e directory /pub/msdos/demos/music/programs/trackers. The filenames are\u003cbr\u003e\u003e ST301.ZIP and MMED101B.ZIP i believe. since you\u0027re using a 386 PC, ST is\u003cbr\u003e\u003e probably the better choice for you.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAre ther any similar programs for the Mac?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCurious-\u003cbr\u003eThad\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~**                  \u0026#34;A child was asked where the light came from...           **    - he blew the candle out and said                                       **                  \u0027Now you tell me where it has gone............\u0027\u0026#34;          **  -----------------------------------------------------------------------   **              Thad Biggerstaff   thad@falcon.cc.ukans.edu                   **                                                                            **    ANY info on Power Macs as Digital Audio Workstations WELCOMED!!!!!      *******************************************************************************\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_14":  {
                         "subject":  "serious floyd",
                         "from":  "SCRUTON@JOYCE.dnet.hac.com",
                         "dateString":  "Mon, 10 Oct 1994 12:43:23 -0800 (PST)",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003efor those who seek the non-classic-rock pink floyd, you must remember that   floyd has really been 3 DISTINCT and DIFFERENT bands over the years;\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e   1981-present :  Non-Roger Waters; basically driven by David Gilmour\u003cbr\u003e                    - basically lacking lyrical content, mostly glisteny                        mellow stuff\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e   1968?-1980   : the rise of Roger Waters, bigtime lyrical tributes to\u003cbr\u003e                    syd, the founder of the band, then more into politics...                     - high-budget production, huge arena shows, etc...\u003cbr\u003e   1965-1968    : the Syd Barrett years; Syd is one of the most gifted\u003cbr\u003e                    musical arrangers/composers who ever lived (he also\u003cbr\u003e                      taught Dave Gilmour to play slide guitar)\u003cbr\u003e                    - extremely weird, long instrumental sets of experimental                       music, no real adherance to musical keys/tempo... with                        the occasional pop tune thrown in.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e   floyd basically had the full multimedia show down to a science wayyyy     back in 1970, with quadraphonic/pentaphonic sound, full 3d projection       of ALL the instruments independently, and visuals (both animation        and stills)...\u003cbr\u003e   they were basically 20-30 years ahead of their time.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e it\u0027s a real shame that their older stuff is forgotten, and even more of   a dissapointment that so little of it comes out in their showz,\u003cbr\u003e   \u003cbr\u003e   altho Roger Waters has played \u0026#34;set the controls for the heart of the sun\u0026#34;     in concert a number of times, and the Gilmour Floyd has played\u003cbr\u003e       \u0026#34;Astronomy Domine\u0026#34; several tours, too...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ejust my .02 bux worth.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSeeya!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eDave Scruton\u003cbr\u003eFractallonomy\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
