  "amb_1994_09_101":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: Michael E. Clay: Thanks and a Beginnings Comment",
                          "from":  "\"Ken Stuart\" \u003cken@snowcrest.net\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Wed, 21 Sep 94 19:04:56 PDT",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eOn Wed, 21 Sep 1994 13:04:05 -0700, \u003cbr\u003ePaul Godwin - New Dog Music  \u003cdog46@well.sf.ca.us\u003e wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003ere: Popul Vuh, can you direct me to info on origins of.  my first contact\u003cbr\u003e\u003ewas through werner herzog soundtracks but i had no idea they were around as\u003cbr\u003e\u003eearly as 1971. also personnel, etc. would be interesting. anyone?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe authority (outside of people directly connected with the band, who are not very public) is Steven Freeman, who I quoted in the posting from his article in Audion #8.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAudion can be connected at Ultima Thule record store:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e(UK country code) + 0533-854545   phone\u003cbr\u003e(UK country code) + 0533-854555   fax\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eremember they are eight hours later than sf.ca.us ...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ethey are open w-f 11:30 am - 5:30 pm, Sat 10am-6pm but fax is always on.\u003cbr\u003ethey have mail order and I\u0027ve gotten most of my Popol Vuh CDs that way...they accept visa \u0026 master card by simply faxing the number.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ethey have plenty of \u0026#34;ambient\u0026#34; \u0026#34;synth\u0026#34; \u0026#34;progressive\u0026#34; \u0026#34;difficult\u0026#34; CDs, but\u0026#34;no techno or house\u0026#34; (not even the Orb).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ePS Ultima Thule was the name of a VERY obscure Tangerine Dream single, so you get the emphasis there...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003erespect to all,\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eKen            ken@snowcrest.net   (primary address)\u003cbr\u003e               (if no answer, try ken.stuart@tigerteam.org )\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
