  "amb_1994_10_370":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: Equipment Question: Delete if offended.",
                          "from":  "Matt Corwine \u003cmcorwine@u.washington.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 27 Oct 1994 09:36:35 -0700 (PDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOn Thu, 27 Oct 1994, Dave Manning wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e So I\u0027m asking the music.community on the list - if I wanted to start with\u003cbr\u003e\u003e something, would this be a good place to start? The cost (\u0026#34;for a limited\u003cbr\u003e\u003e time\u0026#34;) is $499.\u003cbr\u003eWell, in my personal opinion, unless you\u0027re going for that fat analogue sound, I think no setup is complete without some sort of sampling \u003cbr\u003ecapability.  I usually prefer to use samples to \u0026#34;round out\u0026#34; the sound of the track, to create something lush and organic... But that\u0027s just my \u003cbr\u003epersonal opinion... For the cost it isn\u0027t too bad.  I\u0027d want to hear what it sounds like first, however...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ePeace,\u003cbr\u003eMatt\u003cbr\u003eVIS-111 \u0026#34;Integratron\u0026#34; by Matthew Corwine/ATOI Seattle\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_110":  {
                          "subject":  "RE: my top 10",
                          "from":  "Brian Hostetler \u003cbhostetl@silver.ucs.indiana.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 13 Oct 1994 10:39:35 -0500 (EST)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMark Conklin says:\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e 8. Deep Forest\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e 9. Enigma - Sadeness\u003cbr\u003e\u003e I know that Mixmaster Morris doesn\u0027t dig these bands but as far as pop\u003cbr\u003e\u003e ambient goes I really like both. In fact, I\u0027m almost embarrassed to\u003cbr\u003e\u003e admit it to many people, but I play\u0027em a lot more than I play Aphex\u0027s\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Selected Ambient Works II.  I\u0027m glad to see that someone else on this\u003cbr\u003e\u003e list likes them too. Maybe we should go hide now?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWho in the fuck is Mixmaster Morris?  I\u0027ve said it on this list, in\u003cbr\u003enot so many words, before and I\u0027ll say it again.  Listen to what you\u003cbr\u003elike.  MM and most others on this list are arrogant (as far as music\u003cbr\u003egoes).  Just listen to what makes you happy, be it ambient, afx or\u003cbr\u003erock.  I\u0027ll think you\u0027re cool for listening to what you want far more\u003cbr\u003ethan listening to Aphex because everyone \u003ci\u003eelse\u003c/i\u003e says it\u0027s cool.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMy favorite bands?\u003cbr\u003e1. Seefeel\u003cbr\u003e2. MBV\u003cbr\u003e3. Orb\u003cbr\u003e4. old Sugar\u003cbr\u003e5. Curve\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMM and Parry can eat that list, for all I care.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-- \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBrian\u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;Pepsi, just fucking drink it, man!\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003ehttp://sparrow.bio.indiana.edu/brian/me         bhostetl@silver.ucs.indiana.edu"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_68":  {
                         "subject":  "Re: Current Ambient favorites list",
                         "from":  "\"Alan M. Parry\" \u003cfluid@hyperreal.com\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Tue, 11 Oct 1994 22:06:10 -0700 (PDT)",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOn Tue, 11 Oct 1994, Clark R. Wilkins wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Pink Floyd - Ummagumma (anyone seen this on CD?)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e Yep, my brother has it.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e::         Alan M. Parry             \u003cbr\u003e::      fluid@hyperreal.com     \u003cbr\u003e::    \u003cfinger me for PGP key\u003e\u003cbr\u003e::  http://hyperreal.com/~fluid   \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
  "amb_1994_10_114":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: my top 10",
                          "from":  "mbconkli@rs6000.cmp.ilstu.edu (Mark Conklin)",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 13 Oct 1994 13:23:43 -0500 (CDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Who in the fuck is Mixmaster Morris?  I\u0027ve said it on this list, in\u003cbr\u003e\u003e not so many words, before and I\u0027ll say it again.  Listen to what you\u003cbr\u003e\u003e like.  MM and most others on this list are arrogant (as far as music\u003cbr\u003e\u003e goes).  Just listen to what makes you happy, be it ambient, afx or\u003cbr\u003e\u003e rock.  I\u0027ll think you\u0027re cool for listening to what you want far more\u003cbr\u003e\u003e than listening to Aphex because everyone \u003ci\u003eelse\u003c/i\u003e says it\u0027s cool.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eNot my point at all. I like what I like, as you do. To avoid flames, althoughevidently it didn\u0027t work, I started my paragraph with an introductory\u003cbr\u003estatement and a little humor...not much more than that. I respect MM because Ienjoy his music.\u003cbr\u003eDo I always agree with him - well, evidently not. However, am I glad\u003cbr\u003eto see his posts? Damn straight. Relax, I\u0027m not as easy posed as you must thinkI am.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMC\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
