  "amb_1994_10_314":  {
                          "subject":  "IMHO more great ambient",
                          "from":  "Jeffrey Kihn \u003cjeffkihn@ocf.Berkeley.EDU\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Sat, 22 Oct 1994 13:26:24 -0700",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI haven\u0027t heard much mention of this album on the list, and what little\u003cbr\u003eI did hear was rather \u0026#34;ho-hum\u0026#34;, so I just wanted to tell the ambient worldthat\u003cbr\u003eI think _Io_ (an MLO Production) is a seriously excellent album. Rarely\u003cbr\u003edoes a pure ambient album draw me in so much. Very minimal, yet rich andsensitively done. I find it to be more grounding/earthy and less spacey\u003cbr\u003ethan most ambient records, yet not spooky a la Locust.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOh, and before I forget. About Woob. Am I to assume that Em:t just makes their catalog numbers very visible, or is \u0026#34;1194\u0026#34; part/all of the title\u003cbr\u003eof the album? \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e--Jeff\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
