  "amb_1994_09_103":  {
                          "subject":  "XEXnXoX Roach is God",
                          "from":  "Darryl Stephen Roy \u003cdsroy@owlnet.rice.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Wed, 21 Sep 1994 23:12:59 -0500 (CDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eMy second posting from Houston, armpit of the third coast.   (tyhk)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI finally got a chance to listen to a recent acquisition, \u0026#34;Soma\u0026#34;, \u003cbr\u003eby Robert Rich and Steve Roach.  It\u0027s my third album by Roach, the \u003cbr\u003eothers being \u0026#34;Origins\u0026#34; and \u0026#34;Suspended Memories, Forgotten Gods\u0026#34;, his \u003cbr\u003ecollaboration with Jorge Reyes and Suzo Saiz.  Roach has ascended to\u003cbr\u003emy personal pantheon of artists who can seemingly do no wrong.  A nocturnalcruise in an Amazonian basin, whereas \u0026#34;Origins\u0026#34; had a strong subterraineanfeel to it.  Plug over and out.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIf I may briefly introduce myself:  I\u0027m a relative newcomer to ambient music,having developed an immediate aversion the first time I heard some crystalgazing music (Vollenweider and Ciani, perhaps) and held Eno and his clique to blame.  Only in the past year or so has my sustained interest in dub (the Jamaican variety) and traditional ethnic musics led me to seek what had\u003cbr\u003echanged in the field in the intervening years.  So far, I much favor \u003cbr\u003eritualistic, tribal ambience, and some of the permutations that modern dubhas taken to droning synths or auto-archipeggiated space music.  \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI wonder if anyone else out there finds their putatively \u0026#34;ambient\u0026#34; music muchtoo interesting to serve in a \u0026#34;furniture music\u0026#34; role?  For background and/orstudy music, I find I have to put on something I can tune out more easily, like old folksingers or the radio...   \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-- \u003cbr\u003eDarryl Stephen Roy                         dsroy@owlnet.rice.edu\u003cbr\u003e@\u003e-`--,--  @\u003e-`--,--  @\u003e-`--,--  @\u003e-`--,--  @\u003e-`--,--  @\u003e-`--,-- \u003cbr\u003eComputers are useless.  They can only give you answers.- Picasso \u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
