                          "from":  "\"Ken Stuart\" \u003cken@snowcrest.net\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Fri, 28 Oct 94 11:17:25 PDT",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eHello,\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAnyone heard of this one??\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWill there be a third called \u0026#34;Animals\u0026#34;? :-)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eKen \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e----- Forwarded message begins here -----\u003cbr\u003eFrom: EAR/Rational Music  \u003cangst@xmission.com\u003e\u003cbr\u003eTo: ken@snowcrest.net\u003cbr\u003eDate: Fri, 28 Oct 1994 09:11:31 -0600 (MDT)\u003cbr\u003eSubject: Re: Namlook/Schulze\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e Hello,\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e Do you have/Can you get the new Namlook/Schulze CD \u0026#34;Dark Side of the Moog\u0026#34;?\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI can get\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eNamlook, Pete/Klaus Schulze - Wish You Were There[20516]Fax             $16.75 #\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e------ Forwarded message ends here ------\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003erespect to all,\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eKen            ken@snowcrest.net   (primary address)\u003cbr\u003e               (if no answer, try ken.stuart@tigerteam.org )\u003cbr\u003e"
