  "amb_1994_11_100":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: RAVERS\u0027 INTERNET INVASION",
                          "from":  "vilexile \u003ceinexile@netcom.com\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Tue, 15 Nov 1994 00:24:51 -0800 (PST)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOn Tue, 15 Nov 1994 KNoXxb@aol.com wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e\u003eBROUGHT TO YOU BY THE ZIPPY INVASION TASK FORCE:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Who are these guys trying to kid? They remind me EXACTLY of some other\u003cbr\u003e\u003e self-proclaimed _Y_IPPIE leaders known as the Chicago Seven, back in the late\u003cbr\u003e\u003e sixties ...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI wouldn\u0027t go that far, but it\u0027s somewhat an embarrassment. The goofy \u003cbr\u003etone tempts me to come out in support of the act. I\u0027d just like to point out a few things:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. Commenting on the internal affairs of a country not your own is one \u003cbr\u003ething. Becoming engrossed in it is kind of improper. If the British ever become tired of oppressive laws, they will get rid of the folks who are passing them. I\u0027d like to know how many among this zippy task force (what a laughable concept) actually ran for office in the last election.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e2. Consider, if you will, the ramifications of this corny \u0026#34;global vote\u0026#34; concept were it to become reality. Not everyone on this earth appreciates liberty as much as some of us might. In fact, it\u0027s probably safe to say most people view it with contempt. I\u0027m pretty comfortable with the fact that John Major doesn\u0027t have a say in the laws passed in the US. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e3. No one is going to take the internet away. At worst, people will have to pay market value for it someday. This whole idea of mailing lists \u003cbr\u003ebeing limited to ten subscribers might be good for those days when you\u0027re feeling angry but don\u0027t know who to be angry at, but it\u0027s a paranoic \u003cbr\u003eteenage fantasy and everyone knows damn well who and what the Act is \u003cbr\u003eaimed at. If anything, it is this notion of democratic rule as clean and pure as the wind driven snow, that has allowed the greater number of \u003cbr\u003epeople to pass laws which treat the lesser number unjustly.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e einexile\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIf this also went to WSD-L why didn\u0027t I get two copies?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e \u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_11_104":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: fwd - pitch control",
                          "from":  "David F Maier \u003cdfm8@columbia.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Tue, 15 Nov 1994 14:18:01 -0500 (EST)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOn Mon, 14 Nov 1994, Andrew Thomas wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e ------- Forwarded Message\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Date: Mon, 14 Nov 94 13:21:55 -0800\u003cbr\u003e\u003e From: \u0026#34;David A. Craig\u0026#34; \u003cdac@cosmic.physics.ucsb.edu\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e To: ambient@hyperreal.com\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Subject: pitch control\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e I posted the query about the mystery eno song \u0026#34;pitch control\u0026#34; to nerve_net,\u003cbr\u003e\u003e and received the following information from the list\u0027s illustrious leader,\u003cbr\u003e\u003e alex rubli:\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e Pich control appears on the \u0027begegnungen\u0027 album by \u003cbr\u003e\u003e eno-moebius-rodelius-plank.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e So there you go!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHe might have added that \u0026#34;begegnungen\u0026#34; is a compilation album, and that the track originally appeared on the moebius-plank-neumeier album \u0026#34;zero set\u0026#34;, on which Eno does not appear.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eD.\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_09_41":  {
                         "subject":  "Jon Hassell Reply",
                         "from":  "Jeff Holland \u003cholland@spot.Colorado.EDU\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Sun, 18 Sep 1994 20:52:53 -0600 (MDT)",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eAvoid the new Jon Hassell at all costs- It\u0027s called \u0026#34;Blue Screen\u0026#34; and is a melange of styles without any cohesion or direction.  I\u0027ve got just \u003cbr\u003eabout everything he\u0027s released and this one was a dissapointment.  He \u003cbr\u003edoes whine a little in the liner notes about Byrne and Eno doing the \u003cbr\u003eworldbeat thang and leaving him out...  \u003cbr\u003eJefferson\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
