  "amb_1994_11_186":  {
                          "subject":  "other musical tastes",
                          "from":  "Mad Gil \u003ccyberpun@wam.umd.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Sun, 20 Nov 1994 22:07:28 -0500 (EST)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eJust to give a few of you a primer here, I\u0027m coming to the ambient list from the techno-ambient point of view.  I didn\u0027t start off listening to ambient purely.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSo I\u0027m curious...how many ambient listeners out there like or enjoy \u003cbr\u003eclassical music?  IF so, what kind?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI like to read all of the posts that include many recomendations of a lot of contemporary classical (1900-)( I really liked that organ thread).  But some of it seems so detached from  what one considers Classical (capital C, but not defining that period specifically).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ebored in the computer lab,\u003cbr\u003eGil\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eGil Yaker\t\t\\spherical therapy/       Chief Engineer, WMUC Radio\u003cbr\u003ecyberpun@wam.umd.edu \t \\9p-12a thursday/          AM 650 kHz / FM 88.1 MHz orbital@scdh21.umd.edu\t  \\   88.1 FM\t/             College Park, Marylandgil@wmuc.umd.edu            \u0026#34;If you can\u0027t tune us in, you live too far away\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
