  "amb_1994_10_186":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: 99% have NO chance! - high fi equip",
                          "from":  "ebrandt@muddcs.cs.hmc.edu (Eli Brandt)",
                          "dateString":  "Sun, 16 Oct 1994 18:24:42 -0700 (PDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e(Skip to the end for ambient content.)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Up until a few years ago, with the invention of dat tapes, i believe that\u003cbr\u003e\u003e all cd\u0027s were mastered off of video tapes. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI don\u0027t know about that...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e (data on a videotape is written in diagonal lines across the tape\u003cbr\u003e\u003e rather than in a long stream along the tape, very strange).  \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;helical-scan\u0026#34;: the head assemblage spins around, so you get high\u003cbr\u003etape speeds past the head without actually running the tape that fast.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Anyway, point being, you can get near cd quality sound out of a videotape.\u003cbr\u003eMake sure you have a \u0026#34;hi-fi\u0026#34; VCR.  Old VCRs have lousy sound; new\u003cbr\u003eones, as people have said, are quite good.  The noise reduction seems\u003cbr\u003eto freak out a bit if you put weird noises on the tape, but this is a\u003cbr\u003epretty minor problem.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e of course it\u0027s all pretty silly in this day\u003cbr\u003e\u003e and age when you can buy a score of different digital formats on\u003cbr\u003e\u003e which to record your sounds...and the packages tend to be smaller.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBut a VCR is a lot cheaper than a DAT player -- free, if you already\u003cbr\u003ehave one.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOn now: Extreme\u0027s _Trances/Drones_ Rich re-issue.  Good stuff, less\u003cbr\u003eformulaic than his recent (IMHO) work.  Deep shifting Prophet-5\u003cbr\u003edrones, lap steel guitar, other things (some instruments, some\u003cbr\u003eenvironmental sound).  The focus is mostly on the drone side, though\u003cbr\u003ethere\u0027s some melody/harmony/rhythm in the mix.  I haven\u0027t tried it as\u003cbr\u003ebackground yet, but it works for me as contemplative music.  I was\u003cbr\u003ehappy to find that the CD I\u0027d paid $22 for was actually two CDs, 2-1/2\u003cbr\u003ehours...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eNo beats.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e   Eli   ebrandt@hmc.edu\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
