  "amb_1994_09_96":  {
                         "subject":  "Re: cheap \u0027n dirty surround sound a la Eno",
                         "from":  "Andrew Thomas \u003cathomas@ambient.acs.uci.edu\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Wed, 21 Sep 1994 16:23:09 -0700",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e------- Forwarded Message\u003cbr\u003eDate: Tue, 20 Sep 94 23:15:11 EDT\u003cbr\u003eFrom: f18  20-Sep-1994 2307 -0400 \u003ceirikur@ranger.enet.dec.com\u003e\u003cbr\u003eTo: mike@hyperreal.com\u003cbr\u003eCc: ambient@hyperreal.com, karty@u.washington.edu, eirikur@ranger.enet.dec.comApparently-To: karty@u.washington.edu, ambient@hyperreal.com,\u003cbr\u003e        mike@hyperreal.com\u003cbr\u003eSubject: Re: cheap \u0027n dirty surround sound a la Eno\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAKA the Hafler effect.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe third speaker is not \u0026#34;in parallel\u0026#34; with the other two.  You take its plusterminal and connect it to the plus on the left speaker (or the left plus onthe amp)  the minus side goes to the plus terminal for the right channel.\u003cbr\u003eThe amp doesn\u0027t see much added load from this, I\u0027ve never heard of a problem.\u003cbr\u003eThis new speaker then reproduces the information that is out of phase in thetwo channels.  Its level will be lowish.  Place it behind you.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eA slightly more advanced system uses two rear speakers.  Each has its plus sidetied to the plus of the appropriate front channel.  The two minus terminals areconnected together, with an optional L-pad or potentiometer in the wire tocontrol the volume of the rear speaker.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe above is what Hafler\u0027s box does.  That\u0027s the orginal Dynaco QD-1, and therevived QD-1 II.  I have a QD-1 II, and quite like it.  I must say that I had alot of fun just hooking up a third speaker when I was in high school, lo untothese many years ago.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eEirikur\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e------- End of Forwarded Message\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
