  "amb_1994_11_124":  {
                          "subject":  "RE: space daze",
                          "from":  "App-@ix.netcom.com (Timothy Appnel)",
                          "dateString":  "Wed, 16 Nov 1994 23:15:28 -0800",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eYou wrote: \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eOn Mon, 14 Nov 1994 javina@imap1.asu.edu wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e i was looking through the bins the other day and came across a \u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e compilation called space daze...it seemed to have a good collection \u003cbr\u003eof \u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e artists...anyone heard it?\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e jav =\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003eI saw it today.  It\u0027s all a bunch of old stuff.  Still though, if you \u003cbr\u003e\u003edon\u0027t have a whole lot of ambient stuff already, it\u0027s a good start.  \u003cbr\u003eIt\u0027s \u003cbr\u003e\u003eabout 17 bucks for the two CDs, right?  I know Orb\u0027s blue room is on \u003cbr\u003eit, \u003cbr\u003e\u003enot sure which mix though.  Oh well. \u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eYeah I have Space Daze.  Cleopatra Records put it out.  To recap what \u003cbr\u003eI\u0027m told from the inside its meant to be a compilation chronicalizing \u003cbr\u003ethe pre-ambient music days as we know it.  It has stuff From Eno, \u003cbr\u003eHawkwind, Tangerine Dream, and Kraftwerk amongst others.  I think its a pretty good compilation for someone who is just getting into ambient \u003cbr\u003emusic so they can learn the \u0026#34;background.\u0026#34;  I really haven\u0027t gotten to \u003cbr\u003elisten to it a lot yet.  My initial critisms in my first run through is that all the background material is slanted to the industrial vein of \u003cbr\u003eambient music, most of which have stuff out on Cleopatra.  There are a \u003cbr\u003efew other artists I thought should have been on the compilation that \u003cbr\u003eweren\u0027t like Can, and Eno *with* Fripp just to name a couple that come \u003cbr\u003eto mind.  \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThere is an accompanying book that you can get to go with.  I think its a great idea considering what they were trying to do.  As you read you \u003cbr\u003ecan listen.  (Does this mean its interactive media? just joking.)  All \u003cbr\u003ethings aside,  Its a great idea and a pretty good job of executing it. \u003cbr\u003eIts not perfect but I\u0027d suggest it anyone who want to learn more about \u003cbr\u003ethe origins of ambient music or those into the industrial vein should \u003cbr\u003egive it a try.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eApp-\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
