  "amb_1994_11_256":  {
                          "subject":  "irresistible force",
                          "from":  "vcook@arch.carleton.ca (Vincent Cook)",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 24 Nov 94 15:07:39 EST",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eYeah, Just got the new Irresistible Force this past weekend:\u003cbr\u003ehaven\u0027t played it much \u0027cos the new Mo\u0027Wax \u0026#34;Headz\u0026#34; also came\u003cbr\u003eout (the BEST album and label of the year, no question!).  BUT,\u003cbr\u003ewhat I like it so far:  some good \u0027ol dub for ya too, but not\u003cbr\u003eaggressive like Zion Train.  Typical no beats, shuffling along\u003cbr\u003epleasantly type stuff.  Can\u0027t believe the music industry:  banning\u003cbr\u003eit \u0027cos Astral is picking it up sucks.  Apparently the same \u003cbr\u003eproblem here in Canada with the Autechre \u0026#34;amber\u0026#34; lp.\u003cbr\u003eHoping to get it soon on vinyl though.\u003cbr\u003ec-ya\u003cbr\u003ev-\u003cbr\u003edubwise\u003cbr\u003efro\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_197":  {
                          "subject":  "99% have no chance",
                          "from":  "Don Weir \u003cdonweir@sydney.DIALix.oz.au\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Mon, 17 Oct 1994 16:55:30 +1000 (AEST)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e In response to Ken -\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e \u003e Actually, my method is fairly simple and I use this for things other than \u003e music, eg books, beer, etc.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e whatever works, eh?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e \u003e If I see something spoken of highly three times or more -- in a venue that \u003e has a fairly high level of discussion, such as this mailing list, then I \u003e put it in my queue for future audition or purchase.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e like some guitar ambience I\u0027m after discusssed a week ago...(Djat Karem?)\u003cbr\u003e \u003e neither particularly ambient (according to fans), nor has anything to do \u003e with Fripp!  This set off my detector enough that I am ordering it Monday \u003e morning...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e tell me about it, will you?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e \u003e \u003ereproduces the original sound faithfully.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e \u003e Even though I am audiophile, I have to disagree with this.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e It\u0027s the music that moves one not the sound....but the sound can\u003cbr\u003e increase one\u0027s appreciation...  Just shoot for the highest quality, the more realistic (transparency) whilst still music is the primary factor ....\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e catch yar!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e Don\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_222":  {
                          "subject":  "Trances/Drones",
                          "from":  "Don Weir \u003cdonweir@sydney.DIALix.oz.au\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Tue, 18 Oct 1994 12:13:26 +1000 (AEST)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eIn reply to Eli -\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eOn now: Extreme\u0027s _Trances/Drones_ Rich re-issue.  Good stuff, less\u003cbr\u003e\u003eformulaic than his recent (IMHO) work.  Deep shifting Prophet-5\u003cbr\u003e\u003edrones, lap steel guitar, other things (some instruments, some\u003cbr\u003e\u003eenvironmental sound).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHis early stuff I found, has a more refreshing quality about it, too\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eThe focus is mostly on the drone side, though\u003cbr\u003e\u003ethere\u0027s some melody/harmony/rhythm in the mix.  I haven\u0027t tried it as\u003cbr\u003e\u003ebackground yet, but it works for me as contemplative music.  I was\u003cbr\u003e\u003ehappy to find that the CD I\u0027d paid $22 for was actually two CDs, 2-1/2\u003cbr\u003e\u003ehours...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eNo beats.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eyeh, sounds great. Ear/Rat\u0027s done it for about that inc. air-mail to Oz.\u003cbr\u003eDon\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
