  "amb_1994_09_220":  {
                          "subject":  " Looking for specific types of music",
                          "from":  "PSDOMAIN.PSMAIN.KJACKMAN@EMAIL.STATE.UT.US",
                          "dateString":  "Fri, 30 Sep 1994 15:33:08 -0700",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eHi all.  My name is Kendall, and I help to DJ an electronic\u003cbr\u003emusic radio show on KRCL 91 FM community radio in Salt\u003cbr\u003eLake City, Utah, USA.  Our show (\u0026#34;Variables - 2 \u0026 1/2 hours\u003cbr\u003eof mostly electronic music,\u0026#34; Sunday nights from 10:30p to\u003cbr\u003e1:00a) has been around for over 10 years now.  In the past,\u003cbr\u003ewe have played the more popular electronic works from\u003cbr\u003eartists like Tangerine Dream, Jean-Michel Jarre, Vangelis,\u003cbr\u003eKraftwerk, etc., as well as lesser-known artists (as much as\u003cbr\u003ewe can get our hands on).  We have also played\u003cbr\u003eelectronic works from a few fantastic unpublished local\u003cbr\u003eartists.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis show has a sort of mellow feel to it.  That\u0027s not to say\u003cbr\u003ethat we don\u0027t play fast, energetic music (we often do), but we\u003cbr\u003edo avoid playing the more hardcore, sharp-edged music.  We\u003cbr\u003ealso avoid what is commonly known as \u0026#34;new age\u0026#34; music -\u003cbr\u003ethe show that airs before us plays that stuff.  Oh, and we\u003cbr\u003ealso avoid the light jazz or \u0026#34;adult contemporary\u0026#34; that\u003cbr\u003esometimes passes as \u0026#34;new age.\u0026#34;  We tend to avoid music\u003cbr\u003ewith lyrics for the most part.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLately, a lot of music has been coming into the station that\u003cbr\u003eis \u0026#34;ambient electronic,\u0026#34; \u0026#34;techno,\u0026#34; \u0026#34;trance,\u0026#34; etc.  Much of is\u003cbr\u003emellow synthesizer music, ranging from the most ambient,\u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;sonic wallpaper\u0026#34;-type stuff thru fast-paced intelligent dance\u003cbr\u003emusic.  You know - the latest stuff from Orb and other groups\u003cbr\u003etoo numerous to mention.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe are very interested in giving this new electronic music the\u003cbr\u003eairtime it deserves.  Unfortunately for us, most of it ends up\u003cbr\u003ein the \u0026#34;rock\u0026#34; section of the station\u0027s library before we get a\u003cbr\u003echance to see or hear it. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSince we are not very familiar with the ambient/techno scene\u003cbr\u003eyet, we have no idea where to look in the library for discs that\u003cbr\u003ewe could play.  Since it is all mixed in with the rock discs,\u003cbr\u003eit\u0027s a hit-and-miss, trial and error method for us right now.  I\u003cbr\u003ecan look there for an hour and come up with maybe 3 discs\u003cbr\u003eworthy of our show.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCould you people recommend some ambient/techno albums\u003cbr\u003ethat fit the description of our show? (name the album and the\u003cbr\u003eartist - our library is in pseudo-alphabetical order).  Hopefully,\u003cbr\u003ewe can learn enough to help us distinguish in the future what\u003cbr\u003eto look for.  Meanwhile, maybe we can talk to staff about\u003cbr\u003esetting up a new area specifically for ambient/techno/idm\u003cbr\u003emusic.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThanks all,\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eKendall Jackman\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_11_212":  {
                          "subject":  "Rob\u0027t Rich \"Propagation\" -- disappointed",
                          "from":  "\"Jens Alfke\" \u003cjens_alfke@powertalk.apple.com\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "21 Nov 1994 17:38:22 -0800",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eRemember when I was asking for Robert Rich recommendations? I finally pickedup \u0026#34;Propagation\u0026#34; and was pretty disappointed. Instead of the flowing icinessof \u0026#34;Liquid Air\u0026#34; (on \u0026#34;From Here To Tranquility\u0026#34; #2) there is a lot of\u003cbr\u003efaux-Asian percussion and koto laid on. If I could strip that stuff off themix the rest might be more like what I was looking for, but the overall\u003cbr\u003eeffect was too similar to the Japanese Muzak they play in sushi bars.\u003cbr\u003eAre any of his other releases more ambient? (_Much_ more ambient?)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eJens Alfke ........ OpenDoc Mnemonist ....... jens_alfke@powertalk.apple.com\u003cbr\u003e   \u0026#34;Our soldiers are justified in wishing to bring proper justice to\u003cbr\u003e    these errant managers.\u0026#34;     --Xi Ten, Ministry of Economic Reform, China            after 18 factory managers were executed for poor product quality\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
