  "amb_1994_10_381":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: darkambient...",
                          "from":  "vilexile \u003ceinexile@netcom.com\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 27 Oct 1994 05:05:22 -0700 (PDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCrossposting this to 4ad-l for the hell of it and because I hope someone answers my questions. Hope this doesn\u0027t upset anyone...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOn Wed, 26 Oct 1994, Jeff Sartain wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Is C\u0027est La Mort still in business?  A friend told me that their phone\u003cbr\u003e\u003e number has been disconnected...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThey moved to Seattle, I think, and maybe San Diego after that, or vice versa. I haven\u0027t seen anything from them in yeas except for Handful of \u003cbr\u003eSnowdrops\u0027 _Mort en Direct_ (anyone know where I can find the mythical \u003cbr\u003ethird studio album?) but supposedly Dr. Death vol 6 just came out a while ago. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Both projekt and Soleilmoon carry this label...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI think Projekt is now having dealings with C\u0027est la Mort as well. They plan to reissue various Area releases (finally and thank God!) early next year.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ethat\u0027s death, that\u0027s love, say la more...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e einexile\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
