  "amb_1994_10_23":  {
                         "subject":  "Re: Recommendations - Sun Electric",
                         "from":  "mr808@teleport.com",
                         "dateString":  "Fri, 7 Oct 1994 08:25:50 +0000",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003eAfter thoroughly enjoying their contrib. to Volume 8, and the Orb\u0027s Pomme\u003cbr\u003e\u003eFritz (which I understand they had some part in, I\u0027m looking into ordering\u003cbr\u003e\u003eboth of their albums -- would this be a good idea? How does their album work\u003cbr\u003e\u003ecompare to what little I\u0027ve heard?\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eKitchen: Long playing CD: Veers between ambience \u0026 hard electronics (somemight call it techno).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAaah!: Medium length CD: More ambient than Kitchen, more like Pomme Fritzw/o the cheezoid samples, some beat oriented material too\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eO\u0027locco: CDs w/ 7 mixes : Not enough variation between the mixes to\u003cbr\u003erecommend to any but the hardcore Sunheads.  Guest appearance by the Orb.The CD from R\u0026S says that this is Pt.1 of the Sun Electric Reissue series,and the catalog # indicates a 93 release.  Are there more on the way?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAlso of interest:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFlow - Thomas Fehlmann: 33 minute CDep : Unfortunately priced like an\u003cbr\u003ealbum.  I think this has a really different vibe from other stuff in thetechno realm.  Not ambient, but mixed very well, lots of cool sounds.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFFWD - FFWD: More ambient than Pomme Fritz.  The Orb + Robt. Fripp + ThomasFehlmann.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAnything by Maurizio (one of the Sun Electric dudes, I believe).  Check outthe cut on Excursions in Ambience 2.  I experienced an altered state of\u003cbr\u003econsciousness while chopping vegetables \u0026 listening to this...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLooking at your top 10, Harvey, I\u0027d say Aaah! or FFWD would be to your liking.\u003cbr\u003ePEACE - 808\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;Nostalgia IS a disease!\u0026#34; - MR-808\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
