  "amb_1994_09_235":  {
                          "subject":  "Labradford",
                          "from":  "\"Jens Alfke\" \u003cjens_alfke@powertalk.apple.com\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "30 Sep 1994 17:58:52 -0700",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eDave Walker notes:\u003cbr\u003e\u003eLabradford are veryveryvery good.  Having heard absolutely nothing \u003cbr\u003e\u003eby/about them, I saw them last month (they are one of the acts\u003cbr\u003e\u003eopening for Stereolab in the U.S.)\u003cbr\u003e\u003eI was floored -- two electric guitarists and a bassist, loads of effects,\u003cbr\u003e\u003eno drummer.  There melodies were intricate, the textures were luscious, \u003cbr\u003e\u003eand the lyrics were unintelligible.  I have their debut album _Prazision_ \u003cbr\u003e\u003eon order, I\u0027ll post a review when it shows up.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI\u0027ve had \u0026#34;Prazision\u0026#34; for about six months, and it\u0027s as good as you\u0027re hoping.About half is really nice spooky ambient drone, the other half is sort oflaid-back VU-type guitar songs but with the same production as the ambientmaterial -- the whole thing sounds like it was recorded in some vast trainstation or abandoned factory in the middle of the night. Bucketloads of\u003cbr\u003ehovering endless reverb. (For those who dislike those smooth synth chords andsampled ocean waves, this should be just the ticket!)\u003cbr\u003e  The instrumentation on the album is guitar and ancient keyboards\u003cbr\u003e(Moog/Korg/etc) and lots of effect pedals. Vocoder on a few of the tracks.Definitely a similar aesthetic to Stereolab (plus note the titles like\u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;Listening In Depth\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;Experience The Gated Oscillator\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;New Listening\u0026#34;) andit\u0027s not surprising that they\u0027d be opening for SL, or that they\u0027d be thankedin the liner notes to \u0026#34;Mars Audiac Quintet\u0026#34;.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eYou really lucked out ... I got to hear Truman\u0027s Water open for Stereolab.Talk about your unimaginative self-indulgent Sonic Youth wannabes.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eJens Alfke ........ OpenDoc Geometer ........ jens_alfke@powertalk.apple.com    \u0026#34;Try some more! -- the strawberries taste like strawberries!\u003cbr\u003e       The snozberries taste like snozberries!\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e    \u0026#34;Snozberries!? Who ever heard of a snozberry?\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e    \u0026#34;We are the music makers, and we are the dreamers of the dreams.\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_09_12":  {
                         "subject":  "more labels-n-such",
                         "from":  "\"Mike R Quinn\" \u003cmike_r_quinn@code20.nl.nuwc.navy.mil\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "12 Sep 1994 16:31:18 -0400",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003ePS WOW!  This Lotus thing is kicking my ass!\u003cbr\u003eexclaimed rbcIII\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eif you like the Locust, you\u0027ll probably enjoy equally Tournesol\u0027s Kokotsu,also on Apollo (a similar kind of buzz).  Two of my absolute favorite discsare also on Apollo:  More Beautiful Human Life! by Uzect Plaush (unscramblethe anagram to spot a more familiar name?) and The Fires of Ork (Geir\u003cbr\u003eJennsen/Pete Namlook collaboration originally on FAX).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHas anyone out there listened to a CD called Kyema, Intermediate States doneby Eliane Radigue?  It was released by the Experimental Intermedia Foundationon their XI label circa 1991.  An incredibly sedate \u0026#34;deep listening\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003eexperience that I never seem to tire of, very slowly changing and deeplylayered analog synth sounds and subtle noises.  I don\u0027t know if anyone sharesmy enthusiasm for this piece but to me its a classic of the genre.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eoh yeah, I just remembered another label:  Barooni (country?) has put outsome great ambient stuff by Thomas Koner (processed gong reverberations assource material if I remember correctly).  Which leads to the group Main\u0027s(who cite TK in credits on at least 1 release) 2 CDEPs and latest album\u003cbr\u003eMotion Pool (Beggars Banquet).  Their 1st album Hydra-Calm I wasn\u0027t impressedby but to be fair didn\u0027t get to listen to it carefully.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003emike \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
