  "amb_1994_10_48":  {
                         "subject":  "Voice Of Eye info",
                         "from":  "\"Jens Alfke\" \u003cjens_alfke@powertalk.apple.com\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "11 Oct 1994 10:05:54 -0700",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eHere\u0027s more info on Voice Of Eye, now that I have the CD here in front of me:\u003cbr\u003eVoice Of Eye  \u0026#34;Mariner Sonique\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBonnie McNairn: voice, flute, samples, percussion, Squawk Box, String Pipe,sheet metal\u003cbr\u003eJim Wilson: samples, Thing, percussion, sheet metal, Spring Thing 2, guitarWith:\u003cbr\u003eMarlon Porter: percussion, Spring Thing 2, Bass, sheet metal\u003cbr\u003ePaul Valsecchi: guitar, voice synthesis\u003cbr\u003eUre Thrall: Thing, samples\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e(Capitalized instruments are homemade.)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eContact: Cyclotron Industries, Box 66291, Houston TX 77266 USA\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ePart of the reason it\u0027s so hard to describe their sound is the large numberof homemade instruments. Some of them sound like detuned violins or horns,some like nothing in particular. Despite all the credits for \u0026#34;samples\u0026#34; and\u0026#34;voice synthesis\u0026#34; it\u0027s hard to pick out anything particularly synthetic\u003cbr\u003esounding, although the whole sound clearly owes a lot to the judicious use ofvarious effects (mostly reverb, echo and flanging.)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSome of the tracks have too much percussion to be considered ambient (IMHO)but many would be considered quite ambient even to those who are allergic toany kind of a beat.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eInterestingly enough, having listened to several Klezmatics albums over theweekend I note a strong similarity -- not all Klezmer (Jewish folk music) ishappy eastern European folk songs with accordion, there\u0027s a definite strainof eerie wailing Middle Eastern tonalities in it too, and some of the\u003cbr\u003eKlezmatics tracks wouldn\u0027t sound at all out of place mixed in with Voice OfEye.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eJens Alfke ........ OpenDoc Geometer ........ jens_alfke@powertalk.apple.com\u003cbr\u003e         \u0026#34;One does not seriously attack the expertise of a scientist,\u003cbr\u003e                   using the undefined phrase \u0027butt-head.\u0027\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
  "amb_1994_10_330":  {
                          "subject":  "re: \"electronic cafe,\" french text, why no \u0027tranq\u0027",
                          "from":  "terremt@mail.med.cornell.edu (Terre Thaemlitz)",
                          "dateString":  "Tue, 25 Oct 1994 09:50:46 -0400",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eFrom: Alain Mongeau \u003cr23374@er.uqam.ca\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSubject: New York events\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eThe first was some sort of live event featured through the Electronic\u003cbr\u003e\u003eCafe network involving the Future Sound of London at the Kitchen.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eDoes nybody have any sort of update on these events?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ethe NYC end of the electronic cafe will be Nov 4 \u0026 Nov 5 at the Kitchen. I*think* the fsol broadcast is on the 4th. I know it will be at 11pm,\u003cbr\u003ewhichever night. Also, as i had mentioned before, tetsu inoue and I will beperforming at 1am each night - it looks like we\u0027ll be doing more live synthstuff than dj-based stuff this time. I got him to dj - now he\u0027s going toget me to play synths  :)   for more info, here\u0027s the eddress of the NY\u003cbr\u003eorganizer: beneill@panix.com [Ben Neill]\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFrom: Oscillate@aol.com to TeeP\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003ewhy was \u0026#34;Tranquilizer\u0026#34; not on the CD Tranquilizer?\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eBecause Instinct didn\u0027t like it...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003enot only that, but i think they were eager to title my cd Tranquilizer tomilk off whatever hype my comatonse.000 single got, since it was often\u003cbr\u003ereviewed as \u0026#34;Tranquilizer\u0026#34;... I\u0027m glad I got them to put it on plug in +turn on x.2, though!! the whole situation was kinda irking me....\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ebtw: here\u0027s a [functional] translation of that french text under the cd -\u003cbr\u003e        I assemble the poets into a herd, gathering the precious blood oftheir writings for me to piss on.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e        On this surface of congeling red piss, let them slide and marvel attheir divinity. Let them feast on my turds like monks of the Marquis [duSade].\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e        And when the day is over, let them rest their heads in the cloudsand once again find the beauty in it all.  -anonymous\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFrom: TECH137 \u003cST1PK@Jetson.UH.EDU\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSubject: coco,steel and lovebomb\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e        Has anyone heard any of Coco,Steel and Lovebomb\u0027s stuff besides\u003cbr\u003e\u003e  Harlem? I got their full lenth album on Warp records a few months ago..\u003cbr\u003e\u003e        if anyone has this album..let me know whatcha thing about it.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eyeah, i like it quite a bit as well (esp. that very first track!). i agreethat the house tracks are pretty straight forward, but verge on interesting- and i prefer ambient contrasted w/house rather than techno any day!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003epals,\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e     Terre Thaemlitz\u003cbr\u003e     terremt@med.cornell.edu\u003cbr\u003e     http://www2.med.cornell.edu/~terremt/Thaemlitz.html\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_11_129":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: New FAX",
                          "from":  "John Shaft \u003cjds@access.digex.net\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 17 Nov 1994 21:23:54 -30000",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eOn Thu, 17 Nov 1994, Mohsen Gamshad wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Has anyone heard the new FAX CD called \u0026#34;Reoccuring myths of\u003cbr\u003e\u003e urban...\u0026#34;?  Any comments?\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003ei bought this one the other day.  It\u0027s by a guy named Chris Meloche.  The track listing is \u0026#34;Loop 6\u0026#34; -- 73.22.  As it turns out (the sleeve says) \u003cbr\u003ethat this is an excerpt from a 6 hour version which debuted on CHRW-FM \u003cbr\u003e(london, Canada) in May 1994.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ealso from the sleeve: \u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;This is an ambient, environmental electroacoustic work that, once set \u003cbr\u003einto motion, takes on a life of its own.\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ethis is what I\u0027d define as ideal \u0026#34;ambient\u0026#34; -- its continuous, with a low rumbling throughout intersperced with bleeps and reverbed out speech.  \u003cbr\u003eThis is background.  Definitely good for playing with the lights turned out and you\u0027re lying down...  \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eQuestion:  Who is Chris Meloche?  ANy other projects/names?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ejohn\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e------\u003cbr\u003ejohn sweeney \u003cbr\u003e( b i n a r y s o u n d )\u003cbr\u003ejds@access.digex.net\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
