  "amb_1994_09_122":  {
                          "subject":  "ntone (was Re: JOURNEYMAN/MAMA 6)",
                          "from":  "Mike Brown \u003cmike@hyperreal.com\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Fri, 23 Sep 1994 19:16:57 -0700 (PDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003e I have ordered a release called \u0026#34;Antistasis\u0026#34; by Hex on NTone, but my mail\u003cbr\u003e\u003e order house can\u0027t get a lead on it. The review I read for it was *very*\u003cbr\u003e\u003e intriguing... and now I read another glowing review of something out on the\u003cbr\u003e\u003e NTone label -- my interest is really piqued. Anybody know a mailorder house\u003cbr\u003e\u003e specializing in import ambient that stocks NTone releases?\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Thanks, 19.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003eYou can order from NTone / Ninja Tune directly.\u003cbr\u003eThey are even on the net.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe other day I posted an information file / discography at \u003cbr\u003eftp://hyperreal.com/music/labels/ntone\u003cbr\u003e...Go check it out!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThey also sent me a batch of cd\u0027s to review, including the Hex disc and The Journeyman album.  My initial impression of the Hex disc is a mild \u003cbr\u003ethumbs-down, while the Journeyman is a big thumbs-up.  I\u0027ll post full \u003cbr\u003ereviews sometime in the next couple weeks.  The \u0026#34;Ninja Tune\u0026#34; part of the label is their acid jazz division... very good stuff, based on what I\u0027velistened to so far.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMike\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
