  "amb_1994_11_204":  {
                          "subject":  "Global/ Reflective",
                          "from":  "lw94ben@brunel.ac.uk (lw94ben)",
                          "dateString":  "Mon, 21 Nov 1994 16:38:57",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e About the releases on G.C.s old label... It\u0027s called Evolution (Creation isa large UK indie label that put out the Reload EP) and there were 6\u003cbr\u003ereleases, all of which are more or less impossible to find these days. Therewere Reload EPs, a Link EP, a Cyberdon EP, a Global Communication EP andthat sort of thing. Some of the tracks on Evolution made it onto more easilyfound releases, ie Peschi, Mosh and some others were on the Reload LP,\u003cbr\u003eOb-Selon-Minos was the track with the clock ticking on the GC LP, and \u0026#34;TheBiosphere\u0026#34; appeared, in remix form, on Auto Reload Vol 2 EP (Auto Reload Vol1 was an Evolution release).\u003cbr\u003e     Hope thats helpful!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e \u003cbr\u003e Now onto Reflective... theres maybe about 5 releases on this label now? I\u0027mnot sure. There is one album - \u0026#34;Ambiento - A Fax Compilation\u0026#34; - which is, asthe title suggests, a compilation of FAX stuff with Pete, Atmo, Atom Heart(\u0026#34;Coeur Atomique\u0026#34;) and Mr Sharpe all present and correct. My favourite 12\u0026#34;was the Flurescence EP which came out just over a year ago... but was\u003cbr\u003erecently re released so it should prove easy to find. Its by Space Time\u003cbr\u003eContinuum, who is Jonah Sharpe who runs the label... he has done an LP withTerence McKenna, an EP and a new (brilliant) LP on Astralwerks and he\u0027s gottracks on some of the Excursions in Ambience CDs I think... very good music!but he\u0027s a scotsman like me so what do you expect? ;)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThanks for listening!\u003cbr\u003eBrendan Nelson\u003cbr\u003eKinetic Illusion\u003cbr\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
