                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003e the place that the true alternative music is not yet another \u003cbr\u003e\u003e mumble-mouthed angst driven guitar band - perhaps they \u003cbr\u003e\tDang, now where am I going to get rid of these $80 flannels I \u003cbr\u003ejust bought for my mumble-mouthed angst band?   \u003csigh\u003e  Oh the horrors of being an Artiste!   8-)\t\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e And perhaps if, along with more truly alternative venues, \u003cbr\u003e\u003e more RADIO STATIONS would program the music we \u003cbr\u003e\u003e might witness an increase in the number of musician \u003cbr\u003e\u003e working in and pushing the boundaries of the ambient styles.\u003cbr\u003e\tActually, radio is a difficult method to expose some styles of \u003cbr\u003eambient over, especially the nature noise sections.  Most carrier signals aren\u0027t clean enough for this, but oh well.  Such is our lot I guess.  \u003cbr\u003eThis friday, I\u0027m going to do a first on my show:  3 hour ambient mix.  \u003cbr\u003eGoing from the time the Album Preview thingy gets over, until my show \u003cbr\u003eends at 2am.  Wooo Hooo!!!  Mixmaster Dave!   8-)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\t\tGroovy Dave\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
