  "amb_1994_10_255":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: 100% Opportunity For All",
                          "from":  "\"Richard Singer\" \u003cwk03814@worldlink.com\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Tue, 18 Oct 94 21:50:57 -0500",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e Don Weir \u003cdonweir@sydney.DIALix.oz.au\u003e wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eDate: Mon, 17 Oct 1994 20:08:47 +1000 (AEST)\u003cbr\u003e\u003eSubject: 100% Opportunity For All\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eRichard Singer said,\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003esomething or yakking away. They are not listening. Really, there\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003eare very few individuals out there who\u0027ll spend money on hifi gear that\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003ereproduces the original sound faithfully. There are very few music lovers,\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003eindeed there are many who like it.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003eI beg to differ with the gist of this statement.  Not all of us have a\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003elot of money.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eyeh, I don\u0027t.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003eWe have to make sacrificies somewhere, even if it means\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003esettling for inferior equipment.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eor not spending on anything else but food, warmth, shelter, music, sound\u003cbr\u003e\u003eequipment, and computer.  All is sacrificed for this. (I\u0027ve honed it to this)\u003cbr\u003eHmm, perhaps you are more fanatical than I am.  You know, it is a good \u003cbr\u003eidea to buy a book once in a while or take a trip maybe once a year.  \u003cbr\u003eYou might even want to take in a movie now and then (though there are \u003cbr\u003every few good ones, I know) . . .\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eI make time to deal/bargain hunt, seek and listen.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBut sometimes \u0026#34;making time\u0026#34; is impossible.  If you work for a living \u003cbr\u003eand don\u0027t make a tremendous salary, then the more you spend, the more \u003cbr\u003etime you\u0027re going to have to spend working to catch up!  It\u0027s what\u0027s \u003cbr\u003eknown as a \u0026#34;Catch 22,\u0026#34; I suppose (after the book and movie -- one of \u003cbr\u003ewhich you may have seen before you completely \u0026#34;honed\u0026#34; :-) ).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-- Richard Singer\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
