                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Most reviews of \u0026#34;strawberries oceans ships forest\u0026#34; (or something like that), \u003cbr\u003e\u003e credited to \u0026#34;The Fireman\u0026#34;, that I have read indicate that the album is \u003cbr\u003e\u003e rather lame.  I haven\u0027t heard it myself, since the idea of Paul McCartney \u003cbr\u003e\u003e attempting an ambient album thoroughly repulses me...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI\u0027ve heard it and it\u0027s definitely lame, but mostly because it\u0027s a collectionof samey remixes of a single track being passed off as an \u0026#34;album\u0026#34;.  It wasnot distinctly Macca or non-Macca that I could hear.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e--\u003cbr\u003eLazlo (lazlo@rt66.com)\u003cbr\u003e"
