  "amb_1994_08_9":  {
                        "subject":  "Ambience",
                        "from":  "fletcher \u003cfms@MIT.EDU\u003e",
                        "dateString":  "Wed, 17 Aug 1994 10:26:57 EDT",
                        "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eThe thing that I think is neat, and bad, about the name Ambient when\u003cbr\u003eused to describe music is all the different forms of music that fall\u003cbr\u003eunder that name.  Almost every genre of music (save, maybe, heavy metal?)has it\u0027s own ambient variations.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWhat I\u0027m interested in discussing are the common themes inherent in all\u003cbr\u003ethese ambient works.  What has long puzzled me, is that some artists arelabelled as such and then all their songs are compared to other ambient\u003cbr\u003esongs.  Even works produced by the artists which would better be called\u003cbr\u003eNosebleed Acid (or whatever) are still lumped in with all the other\u003cbr\u003eambient music simply because of the reputation of the artist.  Is there\u003cbr\u003eany justification for this?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThere is some justification, depending on how you define ambience.  I\u003cbr\u003esee a couple possible definitions.  One, Ambient music incorporates\u003cbr\u003enatural sounds (by natural I mean any sound not produced by a musical\u003cbr\u003einstrument, garbage trucks are natural sounds) from the environment intoitself.  Two, Ambient music is created as a sonic backdrop that helps\u003cbr\u003edefine the environment in which it\u0027s played.  Those are the two primary\u003cbr\u003emeanings of Ambience that I see used a lot.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSo, certain artists, incorporate natural \u0027found\u0027 sounds into all their\u003cbr\u003emusic.  These artists could, in some sense, be considered Ambient.\u003cbr\u003eOther artists create pieces that contain more texture and pattern than\u003cbr\u003erhythm and melody.  These artists could also be considered Ambient.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI think it\u0027s the interplay these (and possibly other) possible definitionsof Ambience and the way ambient artists interpret them for themselves\u003cbr\u003ethat make the genre of music interesting.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e[fletcher]\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                    },
