  "amb_1994_10_242":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: ambient music and Dolby surround",
                          "from":  "Andy Ressa \u003ci9112959@wsuaix.csc.wsu.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Tue, 18 Oct 1994 10:17:55 -31702 (PDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e  From what I have been able to tell, UFOrb has some pretty complex \u003cbr\u003esorround features on it.  There are many places that I am amazed at the diffrent sounds coming from different parts of the room that just are not there with confentional two speaker systems.  Unfourtunatly my good \u003cbr\u003estereo is at home while I am at school, so I can\u0027t site spesific \u003cbr\u003eexamples... Peace...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=Andy Ressa\t\t\t\t\ti9112959@wsuaix.csc.wsu.edu\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\t\tKeine Macht Fur Dich Mehr!\u003cbr\u003e-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\u003cbr\u003eOn Tue, 18 Oct 1994 CAI@RASCAL.MED.HARVARD.EDU wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e \tI was wondering why people don\u0027t start to make ambient records in the\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Dolby surround format. I would think the surround sound coding will\u003cbr\u003e\u003e greatly enhance the listening pleasure of ambient music.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \tMaybe higher cost for surround coding is the concern here, or\u003cbr\u003e\u003e maybe it is the marketing problem with surround format? Any thoughts\u003cbr\u003e\u003e out there?\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e \tLin\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e BTW, hats off to the people in the MIT and BC radio stations for playing\u003cbr\u003e\u003e wonderful ambient/IDM/trance music night after night.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
