  "amb_1994_10_162":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: fwd - Top something",
                          "from":  "Gordon Kelley \u003cgordon_k@efn.org\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Sat, 15 Oct 1994 07:22:01 -0700 (PDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003ehere\u0027s my fave ambient list(in no particular order):\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSteve Roach-\u0026#34;structures from silence\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003eSteve Roach-\u0026#34;dreamtime return\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003eCocteauTwins-\u0026#34;victorialand\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003eEno-\u0026#34;apollo\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003eEno-\u0026#34;neroli\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003eEno-\u0026#34;on land\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003eHarold Budd-\u0026#34;lovely thunder\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003eR.Carlos Nakai \u0026 Peter Kater-\u0026#34;migration\u0026#34;  (I know, it\u0027s not ambient per se, but it\u0027s so beautiful, and it has the right FEEL)\u003cbr\u003eSuspended Memories_\u0026#34;earth island\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e-------------\u003cbr\u003eHonarable Mention:  Area, Constance Demby, Kevin Braheny, Sheila Chandra, Durutti Column\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAnd what did you think of Aphex Twin\u0027s \u0026#34;Selected Ambient Works 2\u0026#34;?  I did not like it.  In fact, I sold it.  However, I\u0027ve read glowing reviews of it!  Opinions?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eGordon\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
