  "amb_1994_10_443":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: The Moon and the Melodies ",
                          "from":  "Ned Andrew Raggett \u003ceahg119@ea.oac.uci.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Sat, 29 Oct 94 10:46:02 -0700",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e \u003e I\u0027m real new to the ambient side of things and know nothing about\u003cbr\u003e \u003e about Harold Budd. But I came across a copy of The Moon and the\u003cbr\u003e \u003e Melodies the other day and became even more interested when I saw\u003cbr\u003e \u003e it also included Liz Frasier and Robin Guthrie. Is this sort of a\u003cbr\u003e \u003e Cocteau Twins album? Sort of an ambient album? Sort of both? Sort\u003cbr\u003e \u003e of neither? Something completely different?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIt is in fact a Cocteau Twins album [check again and you\u0027ll notice\u003cbr\u003eSimon Raymonde is also credited on the sleeve] with Budd as a \u003cbr\u003ecollaborator.  I don\u0027t know why they decided to credit everybody\u003cbr\u003eindividually on the sleeve.  It\u0027s quite nice--four instrumentals,\u003cbr\u003efour with Liz\u0027s vocals, with Budd\u0027s shimmering piano work standing\u003cbr\u003eout well.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eNed Raggett\u003cbr\u003eeahg119@ea.oac.uci.edu\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
