                         "from":  "rbcIII \u003crobot@svpal.org\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Wed, 21 Sep 1994 11:28:46 -0700 (PDT)",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOn Wed, 21 Sep 1994, Mike Brown wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Off the top of my head, under the name Sun Electric they\u0027ve got...\u003cbr\u003e\u003e   O\u0027Locco (original 1990 release, reissued in 1993 with a different cover)\u003cbr\u003ethe 1990 original is on WAU Mr. Modo and the reissue is on R\u0026S w/out the Dr. LX/Cauty bits\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e   O\u0027Locco (promo only 12\u0026#34; of pts 5-8 of the Orb mix)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ethe Patterson/Cauty bits on R\u0026S\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e   O\u0027Locco (1993 EP with new mixes \u0026 b-sides)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eis this the double clear vinyl on R\u0026S?  if so, I think it\u0027s just called Sun Electric\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e   Kitchen (1993 album)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eif you like o/locco this is the album for you!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e   Aaah! (1994 album-length EP)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCheck out URbeats by Readymade on WAU Mr. Modo for a Fehlmann equivalent of the Kiss EP.  Very cheezy, but quite a treasure.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-robert\u003cbr\u003e"
