  "amb_1994_10_174":  {
                          "subject":  "Neutron 9000 - Lady Burning Sky (review)",
                          "from":  "mr808@teleport.com",
                          "dateString":  "Sat, 15 Oct 1994 22:36:47 +0000",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eOk kids, here\u0027s a review of the latest ambient treat from Neutron 9000,\u003cbr\u003ejust off the boat.  The CD\u0027s on Rising High outta England, and it clocksover 72 minutes.  Surprisingly, there are only 6 tracks, most over 10\u003cbr\u003eminutes.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI was a bit worried when I saw the Les Paul in the instrument credits;\u003cbr\u003eluckily they also have an Electrolux vacuum cleaner!    If you can deal w/the guitar on Roger Eno, you can probably deal w/ the guitar on track 3\u003cbr\u003e(not to say it\u0027s anything like Roger\u0027s slide).  WARNING: track 4 has weirdpoetry all thru it, which ALMOST makes the track unlistenable to me.  Thistrack sounds almost like something Peter Sinfield would do if he were stillaround.  The sound on the album is full and electronic, sometimes bleepy,sometimes percy, sometimes w/ hi-hats, but never w/ kick or snare...untilthe last track, which is a MUCH more mellow version of the earlier beat\u003cbr\u003eoriented N9000.  There\u0027s an ethnic vocal sample on this (not too bad), butalso a tasty 303 line (I\u0027d swear it\u0027s being run thru their SH-09).  It\u0027svery trancey and my fave of the 6.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI can\u0027t really name a comparable album; it doesn\u0027t sound like anything\u003cbr\u003eelse, really.  It belongs to the more modern school of ambience, though;there\u0027s always a pulse running thru the tune.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI don\u0027t know much about N9000; I wish I knew more.  I also have a CD5 and acompilation track by them.  The CD5 is from \u002791, is called \u0026#34;Back w/ A\u003cbr\u003eVengeance\u0026#34;, and has 3 hard hitting tracks that are somewhere between\u003cbr\u003eprog.house and detroit style techno.  The comp. track, from Utd.\u003cbr\u003eFrequencies of Trance, is ambient.  I was kinda surprised that \u0026#34;Lady\u003cbr\u003eBurning Sky\u0026#34; is so mellow.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ePEACEOUT\u003cbr\u003eMR-808\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eNow on Sony: Lady Burning Sky - N9000, of course.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
