  "amb_1994_10_459":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: UVX, Magic Eye label",
                          "from":  "chrome@fluffy.xs4all.nl (CHrOmE!)",
                          "dateString":  "Sun, 30 Oct 94 05:21:33 -0100",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eIn \u003c199410291843.AA21094@world.std.com\u003e chowe@world.std.com (ewoH sirhC) writes:\u003cbr\u003e\u003eJust discovered \u0026#34;Double Helix\u0026#34; by UVX.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eTell me more ...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eI think it\u0027s pretty good. Some of the samples seem to be mixed in in a\u003cbr\u003e\u003eslightly amateurish fashion, but there are some really impressive \u003cbr\u003e\u003eseamless audio morphs from the straight-up 4/4 dance to really spacy DUB!\u003cbr\u003e\u003eIt\u0027s on the Magic Eye label, which seems to put out stuff of consistently\u003cbr\u003e\u003ehigh quality. But, I only know of three releases on this label:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWell I think Magick Eye is owned by Astralasia ... and as far as I know\u003cbr\u003eAstralasia and Magic Mushroom Band are kind of the same thing ... Astralasiareleased 3 fulllength albums on Magick Eye beeing (in chronological order):\u003cbr\u003eThe Polictics Of Ecstasy\u003cbr\u003ePitched Up At The Edge Of Reality\u003cbr\u003eWhatever Happenend To Utopia?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWhich are quite good in my opinion ... Friends of mine call it \u0026#34;hippy-techno\u0026#34;.I\u0027m busy trying to put together a discography for Magick Eye and make someWWW stuff about them, just like I\u0027ve done the Planet Dog discography and I\u0027mworking on Web stuff for that label too ... So any info on Magick Eye isVERY welcome!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eGreetings from Amsterdam, Chrome\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
