  "amb_1994_09_221":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: AMBIENT IS DEAD",
                          "from":  "8bit@vlad.bowker.com (Dan Nicholson)",
                          "dateString":  "Fri, 30 Sep 94 11:41:19 EDT",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eDOG \u003cdog@neoneo.demon.co.uk\u003e writes:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e But more than there music they have elevated themselves above the pack and\u003cbr\u003e\u003e this is because they managed to create a beleievable world (the graphics\u003cbr\u003e\u003e the video work and the music and media reviews) they seem to live and speak\u003cbr\u003e\u003e a new form of communication (there use of ISDN and silicon graphics)why\u003cbr\u003e\u003e can\u0027t other electronic artists be more dynamic.Unless more thought and\u003cbr\u003eIf your definition of dynamic is \u0026#34;living and speaking a new form of\u003cbr\u003ecommunication (their use of ISDN and silicon graphics)\u0026#34; then it is becausemost techno artists are still making their music in bedrooms and basements,not sitting in the middle of a room with hundreds of thousands worth of\u003cbr\u003eequipment. Frank Sinatra uses ISDN, the Rolling Stones have a WWW page -does this mean they\u0027re dynamic? Your message strikes me as that of someonewho has bought into the whole multimedia revolution b/s - ambient is aboutMUSIC not about MTV and \u0026#34;the information superhighway\u0026#34;.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAs the song goes - \u0026#34;the sound of the UNDERGROUND\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e- Dan\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e      transmission 23 - FTZ - edrone - clonor the other - morpheus ii\u003cbr\u003e              The 8-Bit Collective/8-Bit Records * US/Finland\u003cbr\u003e           mail: eightbit@vlad.bowker.com - rkn@phoenix.oulu.fi\u003cbr\u003e      WorldWideWeb: http://ftp.luth.se/pub/misc2/kosmic/www/8bit.html\u003cbr\u003e     KLF/FreeMusicFoundation: http://ftp.luth.se/pub/misc2/kosmic/www/\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_104":  {
                          "subject":  "schoolin\u0027 dub stylee",
                          "from":  "aran@MIT.EDU (Teep)",
                          "dateString":  "Wed, 12 Oct 94 19:44:19 -800",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eREWIND AND COME AGAIN!\u003cbr\u003e\u003eWhat exactly does the word \u0026#34;deep\u0026#34; mean when used in talking\u003cbr\u003e\u003eabout dub music?  Bass-y?  Dark-sounding?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLets kick this one off with the multiple choice answers.\u003cbr\u003e       _\u003cbr\u003edeep (dep)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. extending to or located at a distance below a surface.\u003cbr\u003e2. extending from front to rear or inward from the outside.\u003cbr\u003e3. arising from or penetrating to a depth.\u003cbr\u003e4. far distant; obscure.\u003cbr\u003e5. learned; profound.\u003cbr\u003e6. intense; extreme.\u003cbr\u003e7. dark rather than pale in shade.\u003cbr\u003e8. low in pitch; resonant.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e9. ALL of the above!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMmm, actually this sounds like an essay question. (hold tight!)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWell, in one direction it could apply to the actual sound\u003cbr\u003eof the music being received.  I would say deep as in \u003cbr\u003ecavernous.  The immersion in delay spiraling from the sky\u003cbr\u003einto a conch shell and navigating quickly into your ear canal.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThen of course there is the application of the word deep\u003cbr\u003eto define the FEELING you get listening to dub.  A Hammond\u003cbr\u003eorgan played soulfully gives me that feeling.  A certain mental\u003cbr\u003ebutton gets pushed to trigger a peak experience.  You know,\u003cbr\u003ewhen your soul starts to resonate. That shit is deep.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAt last there could be a more literal meaning to my use of the \u003cbr\u003eword deep to describe dub.  Living in JA can be tough going.\u003cbr\u003eIt renders a particular perspective of the fall of the \u003cbr\u003enew world order and in turn gives birth to a profound musical\u003cbr\u003eexpression.  Deep dub, by people like the black uhuru.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003enow that\u0027s deep\u003cbr\u003eTeep\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;oh we neeeed looooove!\u0026#34; teep deep\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eon now: dj bunyip, playing some old school electro scratch track\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
