  "amb_1994_09_138":  {
                          "subject":  "ANNOUNCEMENT: World Serpent List",
                          "from":  "Beast of Eden \u003cboe666@u.washington.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Sun, 25 Sep 1994 15:10:29 -0700 (PDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eI noticed that this wasn\u0027t included on the list of ambient mailing lists.Ambient artists discussed on this list include Coil, Nurse With Wound, \u003cbr\u003eCTI and Lustmord.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e---------- Forwarded message ----------\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e   The World Serpent Distribution Mailing List is a list devoted to the discussion of all musical artists associated with the World Serpent \u003cbr\u003eDistribution organization and record label. Some of the more commonly \u003cbr\u003erecognized artists include Nurse with Wound, Current 93, Death in June, Sol Invictus, Coil, Lemon Kittens, Danielle Dax, Boyd Rice, and Lustmord.\u003cbr\u003e   This is an unmoderated list; anyone may join.  To subscribe, simply\u003cbr\u003einclude the following in the BODY of your message to Listkeeper@hmc.edu:\u003cbr\u003e    subscribe wsd-l [\u003caddress\u003e]\u003cbr\u003e            Subscribe yourself (or \u003caddress\u003e if specified) to wsd-l.\u003cbr\u003e            The address will default to the address from which you are\u003cbr\u003e            sending the request.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e   If you have any questions or problems, please contact:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\t\u0026#34;ListKeeper-Manager@HMC.Edu\u0026#34;.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e   Some possible coverage topics (well, my own areas of interest, anyway):\u003cbr\u003e        1* Updates/reviews of new releases from WS-associated artists\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e        2* Maintaining a resource database including discographies,\u003cbr\u003e           interviews, articles, etc.  I am already doing this to some\u003cbr\u003e           extent. Extension to ftp/gopher or WWW might also be arranged.\u003cbr\u003e        3* Updates of performances/concerts around the world\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e        4* A meeting place for collectors to discuss/price pertinent items.           (this is by all means inclusive of L.A.Y.L.A.H. material)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e        5* In-depth discussion of the philosophies, political leanings,\u003cbr\u003e           artistic influences/whatever.  WS-associated artists draw\u003cbr\u003e           heavily from pagan/magick/occult themes; some are heavily involved           in resurrecting dada/surrealism within a musical context. Some\t   also have connections to the European New Right strain of political\u003cbr\u003e           philosophy.  Is there a common current here?  What cultural\u003cbr\u003e           archetypes are being tossed about?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e        6* Possible discussion of WS-associated \u0026#34;cover artists\u0026#34; --  4AD has           Vaughan Oliver; World Serpent has Babs Santini and Enrico\u003cbr\u003e           Chiarparin. According to one respondent, \u0026#34;Babs Santini\u0026#34; ==\u003cbr\u003e           Steve Stapleton.  Looking back at works by \u0026#34;both\u0026#34; artists, I\u003cbr\u003e           think it\u0027s highly likely that they are the same person.  Except            who did they get to pose as \u0026#34;Babs Santini\u0026#34; in the C93 TPM liners?\u003cbr\u003e\t7* (this should actually be priority 1 right now) -- Construction\u003cbr\u003e           and maintainence of a FAQ for this list.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e------------------------------------------------|----------------------------    \u0026#34;Categories strain and break...             | Harvey D. Thornburg\u003cbr\u003e     Step out of the space provided.\u0026#34;           | hthornbu@osiris.ac.hmc.edu          -Steven Stapleton (1979)              | dada_x@venom.st.hmc.edu------------------------------------------------|----------------------------"
                      },
