  "amb_1994_10_292":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: David Sylvian\u0027s Ember Glance",
                          "from":  "tntmusic@halcyon.halcyon.com (Kevin J. O\u0027Conner dba Tinty Music)",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 20 Oct 1994 07:55:14 -0700",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003eI had never heard of this one prior\u003cbr\u003e\u003eto it\u0027s inclusion on Top Ten Ambient\u003cbr\u003e\u003eTracks. I\u0027m quite famaliar with \u003cbr\u003e\u003eSylvian\u0027s other work, but I have never\u003cbr\u003e\u003eheard of this one. Does anybody know more \u003cbr\u003e\u003eabout this work?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eProperly credited to David Sylvian \u0026 Russell Mills, \u0026#34;Ember Glance: The\u003cbr\u003ePermanence of Memory\u0026#34; was the title of a temporary installation held at awarehouse in Tokyo in September/October 1990.  I was living in Tokyo at the time, and was lucky enough to see it before its two-week run ended.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe album of the music (composed by Sylvian with Frank Perry) appeared abouta year later, packaged with a book about the installation.  A bit pricey (Ipaid 5800 yen for it, about $48 at the time), but a nice package.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe CD itself is rather short, at about 35 minutes, but is very good - possiblyeven better than the two Sylvian/Czukay albums that preceded it.  The longer ofthe two tracks, the 33+ minute \u0026#34;The beekeeper\u0027s apprentice\u0026#34;, is composed andperformed by Sylvian and Frank Perry, who plays the various bells and gongs(bowed as well as struck - no gratuitous percussion-fest here).  Both this trackand the 2-minute \u0026#34;Ephiphany\u0026#34; were looped continuously at the installation, soyou will be missing some of the experience by having to listen to the pieces inlinear fashion.  Nonetheless, this music, particularly \u0026#34;The beekeeper\u0027s apprentice\u0026#34;, will change your perception of time while you are listening to it. When I attended the installation, I left after what I thought had been about three hours (I don\u0027t wear a watch) - but a look at the nearest clock showed that I had only been there for about an hour.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI don\u0027t know if \u0026#34;Ember Glance\u0026#34; is still in print in the US (its UK catalog no. is DSRM1 - it\u0027s on Venture, a Virgin label), but it may still be \u003cbr\u003eavailable in the UK, or perhaps Japan.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e               Kevin J. O\u0027Conner d.b.a. Tinty Music\u003cbr\u003e             P.O. Box 85363   Seattle, WA 98145-1363\u003cbr\u003e        vox: (206) 632-9369     fax/modem: (206) 545-2868\u003cbr\u003e       e-mail: tntmusic@halcyon.com    tintmeister@pan.com\u003cbr\u003e        k.oconner@genie.geis.com    zzs32874@pcvan.or.jp.\u003cbr\u003e   \u0026#34;Sheesh! The times they\u0027re a-gettin\u0027 loopy!\u0026#34; - Milquetoast\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_150":  {
                          "subject":  "Buried Dreams",
                          "from":  "Tim Zeigler \u003czeigler@ucssun1.sdsu.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Fri, 14 Oct 1994 11:55:45 -0700 (PDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003e I recently picked-up the import cd \u0026#34;buried dreams\u0026#34; by david toop \u0026 max\u003cbr\u003e\u003e eastley on the beyond label. it\u0027s a great, organic-ly ethereal ambient\u003cbr\u003e\u003e soundscape mix. my question is, has anybody else heard this?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eYeah, I picked it up over the summer and have never really found my placewith it.  It incorporates a plethora of organic sound bits, some of whichare uniquely interesting.  It certainly has a dark edge too, and would\u003cbr\u003eprobably be quite fitting for swamp exploration.  Unfortunately, I didn\u0027tbring my boots.  Another time, another mood perhaps.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e_________________________________________________________________________Tim Zeigler                                      zeigler@ucssun1.sdsu.eduSan Diego State University                       tzeigler@ucsvax.sdsu.edu"
                      },
