  "amb_1994_10_294":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: Ambient Radio List ",
                          "from":  "Andrew Thomas \u003cathomas@ambient.acs.uci.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 20 Oct 1994 09:53:47 -0700",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Here\u0027s an idea for creating an ambient radio list that has fairly low \u003cbr\u003e\u003e overhead and distributes the work. I think the \u0026#34;ambient top ten\u0026#34; and \u003cbr\u003e\u003e resultant compilation (thanks Darryl Roy!) was a great collaboritve use \u003cbr\u003e\u003e of net bw - want to try doing the same for ambient radio?\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e If you have an ambient radio show or know of one where you are,  that \u003cbr\u003e\u003e information could be posted to this list. \u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e A few days of heavy traffic, then a compilation and we\u0027ve got a great \u003cbr\u003e\u003e resource for artists, lables, listeners and dj\u0027s.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e WMBR publishes a schedule of all our programs - I\u0027d be happy to excerpt \u003cbr\u003e\u003e the ambient/techno show descriptions and times for a start if there is \u003cbr\u003e\u003e some interest here. \u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e Reactions?\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e soundman mj\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eNot a very efficient use of the net.  A better way to do this would be\u003cbr\u003eto have everyone send info to one person and have that person compile\u003cbr\u003ethe list and post it when it\u0027s finished.  In fact, someone offered to\u003cbr\u003edue just that last week!  See below.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAndy\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-------------------------------------------------------------------------From: PSDOMAIN.PSMAIN.KJACKMAN@EMAIL.STATE.UT.US\u003cbr\u003eDate: Wed, 12 Oct 1994 10:54:38 -0700\u003cbr\u003eTo: ambient@hyperreal.com\u003cbr\u003eSubject:  Radio Lists\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHi all.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI am currently assembling a list of radio shows around the world\u003cbr\u003ethat feature electronic, ambient, techno, trance, idm, etc.  If you\u003cbr\u003ehave any information about a radio show in your area (or if you\u003cbr\u003ehost one), please e-mail me (personally, not to the list)  the\u003cbr\u003efollowing information (as much of it as you know, anyway).  \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e*Special note: Be sure to include the phrase \u0026#34;Radio Lists\u0026#34; in your\u003cbr\u003ee-mail subject header.  This is so that my e-mail program will\u003cbr\u003eroute your message to the correct file.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eRequested information:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. Show Name (if it has one)\u003cbr\u003e2. Type(s) of music played (electronic progressive, techno, idm,\u003cbr\u003eambient, whatever)\u003cbr\u003e3. Call letters (like KRCL)\u003cbr\u003e4. Frequency \u0026 Band (like 90.9 FM)\u003cbr\u003e5. City, State, Country (like Salt Lake City, Utah, USA)\u003cbr\u003e6. Day, Time \u0026 Length (like Sunday 10:30pm to 1:00am, or\u003cbr\u003eSunday 10:30 pm for 2-1/2 hours)\u003cbr\u003e7. Main Host (Full name if possible, internet address if exists)\u003cbr\u003e8. Station Music Director (Full name if possible, internet address\u003cbr\u003eif exists)\u003cbr\u003e9. Station Mail Address\u003cbr\u003e10. Station Phone Number\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThanks everyone,\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eKendall Jackman\u003cbr\u003epsdomain.psmain.kjackman@email.state.ut.us\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e***************************************\u003cbr\u003e*IGEME - The Intermountain Gang of Electronic Music\u003cbr\u003eEnthusiasts.  \u003cbr\u003e*When in Utah, tune in to Variables - two and a half hours of\u003cbr\u003emostly electronic music - on KRCL 91 FM, from 10:30pm to\u003cbr\u003e1:00am Sunday nights.\u003cbr\u003e*Searcher and Stallion, a narrative radio drama backed by\u003cbr\u003eelectronic music, airs from 10:30 to 11:00 each week.\u003cbr\u003e***************************************\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_09_222":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: FAX",
                          "from":  "transmat@teleport.com",
                          "dateString":  "Fri, 30 Sep 1994 15:10:03 -0800",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003eSorry I can\u0027t.  Silence was SO \u0026#34;dodgy\u0026#34; that I quit paying attention \u003e\u003eto\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003eFAX.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003eWow....as far as ambient goes Silence is one of the \u0026#34;creme de la creme.\u0026#34; It\u0027s\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003eok if you don\u0027t like it though\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eWell, since you like it so much, what do you like about it? I do like ambient\u003cbr\u003e\u003emusic but I find \u0027Silence\u0027 to be pretty dull. Not much progression within\u003cbr\u003e\u003ethe tracks, and the initial textures don\u0027t grab me to begin with.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI felt the same way, they sounds just kinda layed there like a cute littl\u0027puppy dawg. I sold it after a few listens. But hey, if some one like it\u003cbr\u003e(FAX does have a devoted following) kewl.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ebleep...bleep...transmat@teleport.com\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_08_10":  {
                         "subject":  "[Jeff Sartain \u003cjss@tivoli.tivoli.com\u003e] (fwd)",
                         "from":  "Andrew Thomas \u003candy@hyperreal.com\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Wed, 17 Aug 1994 22:19:22 -0700 (PDT)",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eJeff, you\u0027re subscribed as \u0026#34;jss@tivoli.com\u0026#34;.  Let me know if you need me to change it...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAndy\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e---------- Forwarded message ----------\u003cbr\u003eFrom: Jeff Sartain \u003cjss@tivoli.tivoli.com\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSubject: Re: Breaking silence and the Future of the list\u003cbr\u003eTo: mike@hyperreal.com (Mike Brown)\u003cbr\u003eDate: Wed, 17 Aug 94 10:37:46 CDT\u003cbr\u003eCc: ambient@hyperreal.com\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e The only flame wars I can see happening (and happening \u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e often) are \u0026#34;ambient purists\u0026#34; slagging off people who have a different \u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e conception of ambient music.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e In such cases should Andy or I step in and say \u0026#34;hey, none of that\u0026#34; or\u003cbr\u003e\u003e would that put people off?\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e Mike\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI think that it\u0027s up to the folks who subscribe to the list to make it\u003cbr\u003ewhat they want it to be.  If someone posts something offensive, you\u003cbr\u003ehave to make a decision whether it\u0027s worth your time to sling mud with\u003cbr\u003ethem (and if it will make any difference to you or to them).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBack to the music... :)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\t~~jeff\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
  "amb_1994_10_88":  {
                         "subject":  "Re: T:ME RECORDS...",
                         "from":  "rbcIII \u003crobot@svpal.org\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Wed, 12 Oct 1994 12:46:19 -0700 (PDT)",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOn Mon, 10 Oct 1994, Billy Cordray wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \tCould somebody give me info T:me records?  Like an address, phone \u003cbr\u003e\u003e #, discography, etc...  Peace...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI\u0027m actually interested more in the EMiT stuff.  Anyone have this?  It\u0027s their ambient sublabel, right?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-robert\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
