  "amb_1994_10_261":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: 99% have no chance",
                          "from":  "\"Ken Stuart\" \u003cken@snowcrest.net\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Tue, 18 Oct 94 22:59:05 PDT",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eOn Tue, 18 Oct 1994 01:30:39 -0700 (PDT), \u003cbr\u003eInterstellar Groovy Dave  \u003ccamde933@goshawk.csrv.uidaho.edu\u003e wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e Another case in point: many people advocate the use of high-end\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e interconnects and speaker cables. Test after test shows there is absolutely\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e no technical advantage to these, but the purchasers can *hear* the\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e difference. I would argue that they have received their money\u0027s worth *if\u003cbr\u003e\u003e        I\u0027d like to get some better cables, just in case they do \u003cbr\u003e\u003esomething, but then again, I have about 8 cables running out of the back \u003cbr\u003e\u003eof my tuner/stereo right now, so I don\u0027t want to be spending $15 for \u003cbr\u003e\u003ethose silly ULTRA-MEGA-TURBO-GEODESIC-KILLER CABLES FROM HELL!!! (tm).  \u003cbr\u003e\u003e        Unless of course, I got them as christmas gifts.  8-)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI don\u0027t want this to turn into rec.audio.high_end or something, especiallywhen my initial reply was that you can enjoy and fully appreciate great music on the most modest of systems, including $12 walkpersons \u003cbr\u003e(walkpeople?).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eNevertheless, I have to comment that I\u0027ve read about many flaws \u003cbr\u003ein those \u0026#34;tests\u0026#34;.  IMHO interconnect cables have more differences than \u003cbr\u003emost components (speaker cables less so).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e        Anyway, what\u0027s a favorite brand of speakers for people?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWell, my favorite brand is Quad, but I can\u0027t afford $3500. :-) \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI also like Infinity and Magnepan, both of which make VERY expensive \u003cbr\u003espeakers AND relatively inexpensive speakers using the same technology.\u003cbr\u003eFor example, in my car, I have Infinity car speakers (about $150/pair) \u003cbr\u003ewhich use the same design of ribbon tweeters as their $50K speakers.\u003cbr\u003eIn my house, I have the bottom-of-the-line Magnepan speakers ($500/pair)which use the same midrange driver as the top-of-the-line ones.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e( BTW, in an audiophile magazine, Magnepan received the highest rating \u003cbr\u003e(92%) in response to the question \u0026#34;Would you buy another product from this company?\u0026#34;. )\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIn short, it is better to get a bargain system at a high-end store, than to get the best system at Crazy Josef\u0027s all-made-in-Serbia boombox store.\u003cbr\u003e-\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003erespect to all,\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eKen            ken@snowcrest.net   (primary address)\u003cbr\u003e               (if no answer, try ken.stuart@tigerteam.org )\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_10_461":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: Fave speakers...",
                          "from":  "Kelly Thomas Money \u003cummoney@cc.UManitoba.CA\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Sun, 30 Oct 1994 01:14:40 -0500 (CDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eIn my opinion, I find the Klipsch KG1\u0027s to be an excellent bass performer. Although they are small and only carry 80-100 watts, they are superb foranyone who has a low-end system, yet wants to upgrade to a more potent\u003cbr\u003esound.  I bought my pair for $350.00 Canadian, they were regular\u003cbr\u003e$550/pair, but I bought the demos.  When I buy a new amp these will be myrear monitors.  For anything enhanced with BASE, they are dreamy.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eVector Audax\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eummoney@cc.umanitoba.ca\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
