  "amb_1994_10_430":  {
                          "subject":  "as falls wichita",
                          "from":  "Victoria \u003cVPOLIAKOVA@CENTER.COLGATE.EDU\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "28 Oct 1994 20:17:17 -0400 (EDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCan Pat Metheney be considered ambient?  Some of his stuff, especially\u003cbr\u003eAs Falls Wichita album is very much electronic, has a *mood* and trippy\u003cbr\u003equality.   Surprisingly, my History of Jazz course had Metheney as \u003cbr\u003eone of the required listenings..  and perhaps he does touch on jazz..\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ei am selecting pieces for my Ambient Lounge show, hence the question above.\u003cbr\u003eVictoria\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
