  "amb_1994_09_72":  {
                         "subject":  "Re: Juno Reactor",
                         "from":  "jbuzza@cix.compulink.co.uk (Jon Burrell)",
                         "dateString":  "Tue, 20 Sep 94 21:55 BST-1",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003eWhat\u0027s up on the new Juno Reactor?  Is it worth paying import prices \u003cbr\u003e\u003efor it?  \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAre you referring to Luciana - this was put out a few months ago now ? If so, it\u0027s a one track (60 min) collaboration with Ben Watkins, Dr LX \u003cbr\u003ePatterson, Fletcher, Stefan Holweck. \u003cbr\u003eThe track has an industrial sound reminding me of those scenes from \u003cbr\u003eEraserhead with the steamy,dark factory sets. There is little development from the core mechanical rhythm. Sounds are overlaid continuously and it is these that provide the interest over the harsh, monotonous backdrop. \u003cbr\u003eTry and pick up 2nd hand rather than pay import prices IMO. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eJon Burrell (jbuzza@cix.compulink.co.uk) \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
