  "amb_1994_10_395":  {
                          "subject":  "3 new FAX CD\u0027s!",
                          "from":  "XdadaX@aol.com",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 27 Oct 1994 23:49:37 -0400",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eJust got the four new ones from Fax and they\u0027re goodies.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. The Dark Side Of The Moog  CD (Namlook/Klaus Shulze) This is great. Aclassic. Buy this immediately. Suprisingly there are some heavy beats in allthe droning/ambient/experimental/melody stuff. Really a great one.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e2. Namlook - Autumn CD (Namlook solo)The third in the Seasons Greeting seriesand the best of the three. Ambience with some experimental guitar tinkeringthen a slow building up to a climax. Great.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e3. Wechselspannung - CD (Namlook/Jonah Sharp) Starts out really\u003cbr\u003eexperimental-a bit Aphex sounding in places, then about halfway through amelody comes in for the rest of the CD with lots of beats. A little Autechresounding in places too. Excellent.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e4. Syn - 5 12\u0026#34; (Namlook solo) Starts out ambient and goes into some tranceybits then back to ambient. Reccomended. A good deal as both tracks clock inaround 15 each-30 mins of music!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ehave fun\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003exdadax\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
