  "amb_1994_10_105":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: Pink Floyd",
                          "from":  "\"Ken Stuart\" \u003cken@snowcrest.net\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Wed, 12 Oct 94 23:53:09 PDT",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eOn Mon, 10 Oct 1994 17:25:55 -0700 (PDT), \u003cbr\u003eJoseph Morrison  \u003cbrapman@netcom.com\u003e wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eOn Fri, 7 Oct 1994 transmat@teleport.com wrote:\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e I bought the XXth Aniv. edition CD of Dark Side of the Moon last  year. It\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e is \u0026#34;far out!\u0026#34; Has anyone noticed how \u0026#34;acid like\u0026#34;  the 2nd track - On the\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e Run - must be those VCS3 filters?\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003e bleep...bleep...transmat@teleport.com\u003cbr\u003e\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003eI also got this, but I preferred the original more; this version seemed \u003cbr\u003e\u003eto lack warmth to me.  \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eYes, I was distinctly underwhelmed by the XXth Aniv. CD.  It just sounds a little, well, dull.  I think that maybe the original master tape is \u003cbr\u003efinally getting a little worn out - there have been so many \u0026#34;original \u003cbr\u003emaster\u0026#34; LPs and CDs of this album over the last 20 years.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIn any event, none of the various pressings of Dark Side of the Moon can hold a candle to the Quad version (only on British LP).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWhen played through a good surround (or optimally \u0026#34;SQ\u0026#34;) system, the \u003cbr\u003ereaction is generally \u0026#34;oh yeah, this is what it is supposed to sound like\u0026#34;.If my information is correct, Parsons originally mixed the album in Quad, and the stereo version was done later as an afterthought.  There were also Quad versions of Atom Heart Mother and Wish You Were Here (but no Meddle :-( ).  So, look carefully in those used LP bins...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eObAmbient: \u0026#34;Any Colour You Like\u0026#34; from Dark Side of the Moon...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e-\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003erespect to all,\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eKen            ken@snowcrest.net   (primary address)\u003cbr\u003e               (if no answer, try ken.stuart@tigerteam.org )\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
  "amb_1994_09_71":  {
                         "subject":  "Re: Fishology",
                         "from":  "terremt@mail.med.cornell.edu (Terre Thaemlitz)",
                         "dateString":  "Tue, 20 Sep 1994 16:22:03 -0400",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003eI just heard a track on the radio called (I think) Fishology by Dream\u003cbr\u003e\u003eFish..?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eyes, fishology is from the album dreamfish on rising high records.\u003cbr\u003eDreamfish is Mixmaster Morris (Irresistible Force) and Pete Namlook (FAX).My personal favorite on that album is the first track - \u0026#34;School of fish.\u0026#34;The progression of the track is fucking brilliant!!!!! (and that first\u003cbr\u003e10seconds makes me orgasm, if I may admit such to the group  :)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eyou can get the irresistible force cd on rising high, or on instinct in theUS. there is a dreamfish 2, but it has been tied up in legalities\u003cbr\u003e(apparently Pete and Morris are trying to keep rights on it, but rising\u003cbr\u003ehigh is being piss-assey.)  It was actually all set to be released in theUS on instinct as well, but then the lawsuit started so all hope has beenlost for now.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ebtw: instinct is starting a series of FAX releases, such as a double cd setof Air 1\u00262, and some \u0026#34;new\u0026#34; x2cd compilations of FAX stuff. so alot of FAXstuff should be out and about in the US at a good price  :)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e     Terre Thaemlitz\u003cbr\u003e     terremt@med.cornell.edu\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
