  "amb_1994_10_13":  {
                         "subject":  "Re: dub thoughts",
                         "from":  "Wallace Winfrey \u003cwally@taz.hyperreal.com\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Mon, 10 Oct 1994 12:01:49 -0700 (PDT)",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003eYes this is a very good album!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMy first introduction to dub when I bought this way back in 87. I hadn\u0027t experimented with mood-altering chemicals yet so it really didn\u0027t do much for me then (I was looking for some reggae to add to my mostly hardcore punk collection). Then, during my freshman year in college, I pulled it out to see what I had bought and never really listened to. What a \u003cbr\u003esurprise! As the waves of dubby riddims washed over my thouroughly \u003cbr\u003eganja-soaked consciousness I realized what power the grooves on this \u003cbr\u003evinyl contained. This led to a pursuit of all things dubby as I hunted \u003cbr\u003edown more records including Prince Far I and the Mad Professor. This \u003cbr\u003egreat love I developed for dub (as a result of this album) led to a \u003cbr\u003ecareful and cautious acceptance of \u003cegads\u003e *techno* music when Towers of Dub first hit my eardrums. I turned from my ways of Deadheadness and \u003cbr\u003ebegan the plunge into \u003cahem\u003e ambience. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMy favorite dub picks this week:\u003cbr\u003ePath - Pleasant 12\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003eZion Train/Diatribe split 12\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ewhat i\u0027m listening to: Global Network Operations from ITR (ok, it\u0027s only halfway ambient =P ) \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ewallace winfrey\t\t\t      -------\u003etranscendental express\u003c-------\u003cbr\u003ewally@hyperreal.com                   ambience every saturday morning from c512571@showme.missouri.edu           11am - 1 pm on KCOU 88.1 Columbia, MO\u003cbr\u003e        \u0026#34;we\u0027re not dropping out...we\u0027re infiltrating and taking over\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
