  "amb_1994_10_26":  {
                         "subject":  "Re: More Rawk Music",
                         "from":  "\"Dana WATANABE\" \u003cDWATANAB@uci.edu\u003e",
                         "dateString":  "Mon, 10 Oct 94 15:35:21 PDT",
                         "content":  "\u003cbr\u003emr808@teleport.com said:\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Why the FUCK are we wasting bandwidth talking about rawk here?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003edefine \u0026#34;rawk\u0026#34; music....\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e_MY_ definition does NOT exclude ambient stuff\u003cbr\u003enor does my definition of \u0026#34;ambient music\u0026#34; exclude rock stuff\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI\u0027m sorry, but Eno was in a Rock band....\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Find the appropriate Usenet group if you want to talk rawk.  Otherwise,\u003cbr\u003e\u003e we\u0027re going to be having posts about how the Stones\u0027 new album is as good\u003cbr\u003e\u003e as Some Girls and that\u0027s PROOF that rock is alive \u0026 well blah blah blah.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Can\u0027t we draw the line somewhere?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWell.. the stones have that Paul Oakenfold trance remix...\u003cbr\u003e:)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003eObviously this is not the forum to discuss rock music.\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003e Thank you.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003edisagree there, but i always think labeling is silly\u003cbr\u003eas soon as you use it to limit something\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003eIf we look at the ingredients that have gone into the mix we call ambient\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003etoday, there are an awful lot:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e- Space music (Hawkwind, Tangerine Dream, ...)\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e- Prog-rock (_NEU!_, Can, Popol Vuh, Pink Floyd...)\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e- Industrial (Cab Voltaire, Throbbing Gristle...)\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e- Guitar-rock (Sonic Youth, Cocteau Twins...)\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e- Metal (Killing Joke, Scorn...)\u003cbr\u003e\u003e \u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003e Okay, nice list.  Now what makes Sonic Youth or Throbbing Gristle ambient\u003cbr\u003e\u003e for you?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eNoticeably you don\u0027t pull out floyd or scorn or hawkwind, \u003cbr\u003edefinite rock bands to me...\u003cbr\u003eesp. Floyd and Hawkwind\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ei already went off on how cool Sonic Youth/Thurston Moore was\u003cbr\u003ein regards to an ambient setting... so...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eTG... Ambient? Well.. hmmm...\u003cbr\u003eMusically, i think Hamburger Lady has got some incredible ambient soundsits just that bit in the vocals about the lady\u003cbr\u003egetting all burned up that seems kinda anti-ambient\u003cbr\u003ebut i do think a lot of their stuff sans-beat is \u003cbr\u003epretty ambient, albeit dark\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAlso, kinda related is the new Exist Dance 12\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003eCap\u0027m Stargazer vs Commander Mindf*ck...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAllied together against Nivar the Floor Killer\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eamazing track (to me) that is basically noisy acidy stuff\u003cbr\u003ethrown around a couple (?) of cheesy guitar solos\u003cbr\u003eand some distorted guitar running around in the background...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ei love it.. i think it works wonderfully...\u003cbr\u003edon\u0027t know what type of music to call it,\u003cbr\u003ebut i bet a bunch of people on here would love it to\u003cbr\u003eand i would NEVER call it\u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;intelligent dance music\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e             ~~~~~\u003cbr\u003ecuz it\u0027s not...\u003cbr\u003ei guess it\u0027s just noisy industrial stuff\u003cbr\u003eor however it was that greg earle described\u003cbr\u003eMike Kandel\u0027s set here in LA a couple months ago...\u003cbr\u003ebut i think it\u0027s got an ambient flavour to it,\u003cbr\u003eit just shouldnt be played in a chill out room\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ei dunno.. i think there is a lot of good \u0026#34;rock\u0026#34; stuff\u003cbr\u003ethat sounds great when mixed in with ambient,\u003cbr\u003eor even on its own as ambient, \u003cbr\u003eand saying \u0026#34;don\u0027t talk about the rolling stones on here\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003eas a blanket statement seems kinda..\u003cbr\u003ei dunno...\u003cbr\u003esilly\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eblankets may be the one thing you need when traveling\u003cbr\u003earound the universe...\u003cbr\u003ebut they\u0027re lousy for statements\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eoh wait.. that\u0027s towels\u003cbr\u003ei forget that linus wasn\u0027t in that book\u003cbr\u003ene\u0027er mind\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e ,\u003cbr\u003edana\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u0026#34;Do you remember that part of the song, the one with that crackling sound? It\u0027s just Not Right that someone can do that to me.\u0026#34;\u003cbr\u003e"
                     },
  "amb_1994_09_108":  {
                          "subject":  "Re: XEXnXoX Roach is God",
                          "from":  "David F Maier \u003cdfm8@columbia.edu\u003e",
                          "dateString":  "Thu, 22 Sep 1994 13:40:06 -0400 (EDT)",
                          "content":  "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eJust figured out your subject - clever!  I like Roach too; check out \u003cbr\u003eDreamtime Return and Strata (the first Rich collaboration), as well as \u003cbr\u003eRich himself.  I actually think Rich is the better talent - Numena and \u003cbr\u003eGaudi are brilliant, and Rainforest, Geometry, and Propagation aren\u0027t bad either.  (I still prefer the best of Eno to any of these, though.)  I \u003cbr\u003ealso don\u0027t mind either drones or sequencers *if used imaginatively* - I agree that much present spacemusic is unimaginative, but I love a good \u003cbr\u003edrone 8-).  Also check out Paul Schutze and some of the other stuff on \u003cbr\u003eExtreme records - some of that is sort of techno-ethnic, but in a \u003cbr\u003edifferent way than Roach et al.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eD.\u003cbr\u003e"
                      },
